title: vichyssoise
directions: Cook potatoes in water or broth until soft. Cool slightly (so as not to crack blender); blend until smooth. Mixture will be like glue! Use some of the milk to clean out the blender. Saute the onion in the butter until tender.

Combine onion and potato mixture to remaining milk and cream. Heat very slowly, stirring frequently, to prevent sticking. Add salt to taste. Add minced celery and parsley at end of cooking time. This soup is excellent served either hot or cold. Makes 2 quarts.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt margarine.
Combine with stuffing.
Spray Pam in 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Put half of stuffing mixture in bottom of dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over stuffing in dish. Put remaining stuffing on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: crumb cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Fill cupcake tins with paper liners. Mix the egg, 1/4 cup sugar and water in a large bowl.
Add biscuit mix and stir well.
Using a metal or plastic measuring cup, fill cupcake holders half full with batter.
Set aside.

title: easy punch
directions: Put sugar, acid and jello in a gallon jug, adding enough water to mix.
Add pineapple juice and finish filling with water.
Add food coloring, if needed.
Add 1/2 cup sugar, if needed.
Freeze 24 hours.
Thaw 1 to 2 hours before needed.
Place in punch bowl and add 1 bottle of 7-Up.

title: powdered sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening, butter and sugar.
Add beaten egg, salt and vanilla.
Sift soda, cream of tartar and flour together.
Add to other mixture.
Roll into small balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press with fork.
Trim with nut meats, etc. if desired.
Bake in 375° oven for 8 to 10 minutes. Makes 3 dozen medium size cookies.

title: crunchy apple crisp(dessert)
directions: Place pie filling in shallow 1-quart baking dish.
In a bowl, combine oats, flour, sugar, spices and salt.
Cut in butter and mix well.
Spread topping evenly over apple filling.
Bake in 355° oven about 30 minutes.
Serve warm/cold.
Makes 6 servings.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Tear cake into pieces.
Mix pudding mix and milk.

title: upside-down apple pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 9-inch pie pan, combine pecans, brown sugar and margarine.
Spread evenly over bottom of pan. Prepare pie crust for 2 crust pie.
Place bottom crust over pecan mixture in pan.
In large bowl, combine apples, sugar, flour and cinnamon.
Mix lightly.
Spoon into pie crust lined pan.
Top with second crust.
Cut slits in several places.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool pie upright in pan for 5 minutes.
Place serving plate over pie.
Invert.
(You may need to take a knife between pan and crust before inverting it.) Carefully remove pan. Some nuts may remain in pan.
Replace on pie with knife.
Cool before serving.

title: gingerbread cookies
directions: Heat syrup (do not boil). Pour over bacon drippings.
Add baking soda, salt, ginger and flour.
Roll and cut.
Bake at 350°.

title: quick english toffee
directions: Sprinkle nuts in buttered 9-inch pie plate.
In a heavy 1 1/2-quart saucepan, melt butter; add sugar.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, to 290° on a candy thermometer (hard crack).
Pour toffee over nuts.
Sprinkle with chocolate pieces; when melted, spread with a spatula.
Cool.
Refrigerate to set chocolate.
Break into pieces.
Wrap and store in refrigerator.

title: macaroon pie
directions: Combine crackers, dates and nuts.
Gradually add sugar to whites while beating continuously.
Add almond extract. Gradually fold in crackers and date nut mix.
Pour into greased pie plate.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° in preheated oven.

title: german chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and flavorings and buttermilk.
Mix.

title: honey chicken
directions: Wash chicken pieces and pat dry.
Double line pan with foil. Melt margarine in pan; stir in remaining ingredients.
Roll chicken pieces in mixture to coat both sides.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour until tender and glazed.

title: french toast casserole
directions: Prepared ahead. Layer bread 2 slices deep in a buttered 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Beat eggs with milk, sugar, salt, vanilla and cinnamon. Pour over bread. Dot with butter.
Cover and refrigerate for 4 hours or overnight. Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Delicious for a brunch.

title: dig deep salad
directions: Layer lettuce, onions, green peppers, water chestnuts, green peas and celery in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread mayonnaise over top layer.
Sprinkle with Romano cheese and sugar.
Do not stir.
Cover and refrigerate 24 hours.
Remove from refrigerator 45 minutes before serving.
Garnish with sliced eggs, bacon and tomatoes.

title: dump cake
directions: Melt 3 tablespoons butter in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Brush over bottom and up sides of pan.
Spread crushed pineapple over bottom of pan.
Spoon cherry pie filling over pineapple.
Mix and spread dry cake mix over fruit.
Spread chopped nuts over mixture.
Spoon 1/2 pound melted butter over all.
Bake in slow oven at 300° for about 1 hour or until crusty brown.

title: ida's sausage bread
directions: Mix together the ingredients.
Roll in balls the size of walnuts.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: granola
directions: Mix
the
dry
ingredients
together.
Mix
the
last 3 ingredients together and stir into dry ingredients.
Bake in a 13 x
9-inch pan for about 25 minutes or until light brown at 300°, stirring every 15 minutes or so.
When granola is brown, add
1 cup of raisins and bake for about 5 minutes.
Allow to cool before storing.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown beef and chopped onion; season as preferred.
Drain. Place in casserole dish; spread evenly.
Put corn over this.

title: haupia
directions: *To make coconut
milk:
Add enough water to a 12-ounce can of coconut milk to make 1 quart liquid (4 cups).

title: green tomato pie
directions: Line pie plates with crust.
Slice tomatoes very thin.
Make layers of tomatoes, sugar and cinnamon until plate is full. Put on top crust and ventilate.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until crust is done.

title: chicken or turkey caruso
directions: In saucepan, heat chicken broth to boiling; add macaroni.
Cook 10 minutes or until tender.
Do not drain.
In large skillet, fry bacon until crisp.
Add green pepper and onion.
Cook and stir until onion is tender; drain off excess fat.
Stir in macaroni-broth mixture and remaining ingredients.
Heat through. Makes 6 to 8 servings.
Excellent for leftover turkey.

title: sherri's carrot casserole
directions: Cook carrots and broccoli and drain.
Saute onion in margarine and add to carrots and broccoli.
Stir in soup and milk.
Cut cheese in small pieces and stir into casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or microwave on High for 8 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 375 for 40 minutes.

title: dang good pie
directions: Pour in uncooked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: orange ambrosia mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin.
Add orange sherbet and 1 can oranges.
Pour into a six cup mold.
Combine rest of ingredients and chill at least 3 hours.
Unmold ring and pile ambrosia in the middle.

title: al's "everything sandwich"
directions: On one side of the bread, spread pizza sauce of your choice. Layer pepperoni over pizza sauce, then spread salami, ham and cheese.
Combine meatballs, spaghetti sauce, onions, hot pepper rings and mushrooms.
Layer meatball mixture over cheese.
Add lettuce, tomato slices and Italian dressing.

title: mud pie
directions: Crumble Oreos.
Layer the cookies on the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan (save a few to decorate the top).
Sprinkle the melted margarine over the cookies.
Cut the ice cream.
Layer it over the cookies.
Freeze until ice cream is hard.
Spread fudge sauce over ice cream.
Freeze again.
Spread Cool Whip.
Sprinkle remaining 0reos on top.
Freeze.

title: the best stick-in-your-throat new york style cheese cake
directions: Now here's the patented trick!
Beat the cream cheese with 1/2 cup heavy cream on medium speed with electric beaters until smooth (or use a fork and hand beat 5622 strokes).
Add the sugar as you're beating.
Scrape the bowl frequently.
In a separate bowl, mix and beat the eggs, vanilla and cornstarch (EVC).
Again, energize the electric beaters and beat the cream cheese as you're pouring in the EVC (or use a fork and hand beat 5622 strokes). Scrape the bowl frequently.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a 9-inch spring-form pan; line with crust of your choice and pour in cheese mixture.
Place on oven rack.
Add hot water to large pan to depth of 1 and 1/2 inches.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.
Turn off oven and leave in cake, with door closed, one more hour.
Remove cheese cake from water bath to wire rack to cool completely.

title: spaghetti squash with brandy cream sauce
directions: Cut squash in half lengthwise and discard seeds.
Place squash, cut side down, in a Dutch oven.
Add water, about 2-inches, bring to a boil, cover and simmer about 20 minutes until tender.
Drain squash, using a fork, remove spaghetti-like strands and set aside.

title: extra crispy pickles
directions: Cover cucumber	with
gallon boiling water and salt. Let stand 1
week.
Drain
and	rinse.	Cover with 1 gallon of boiling water
and alum.
Let stand 24 hours.
Drain.
Combine all ingredients except 3 cups sugar.
Bring to a boil and pour over pickles.
Let stand 24 hours.
Pour off vinegar and bring to a boil
adding
cup sugar.
Repeat 3 times, adding 1 cup sugar each time.	Seal third day.

title: holiday meat balls
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients. Form into bite-sized meat balls, using rounded teaspoonful. Place in shallow baking pan brushed with oil. Bake in preheated 450° oven for 15 minutes or until cooked through.

title: ice cream wafers
directions: Mix in order given.
Beat vigorously.
Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheet.
Allow room to spread.
Bake at 325° to 350° approximately 10 minutes in a moderate oven.
This makes a delicate light cookie with a brown edge.
Serve with ice cream.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Sift together flour, salt, baking powder and cocoa together.
Add eggs, one at a time to creamed mixture.
Add dry ingredients alternating with milk and vanilla.
Beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
Pour in tube pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until done when tested.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs with a spoon.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon; add to egg mixture.
Then add vanilla, nuts and apples.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: honey and mustard pork tenderloin
directions: Trim all visible fat from tenderloin; sprinkle with pepper. Spray nonstick skillet with vegetable spray.
Add oil and heat on medium-high.
Brown tenderloins in skillet for about 10 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Put all ingredients in a pan, except green beans, and boil for 20 minutes.
Add green beans and bake for 20 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except crabmeat (fold it in last), and cover with cheese.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook until it threads.
Add 1 pound raw peanuts.
Cook until light brown; take off heat.
Add 2/3 stick butter; stir until butter is dissolved.
Then add 2 teaspoons soda and stir.
Pour on greased pan.

title: diet cottage cheese pie
directions: Measure 1/2 cup of pineapple juice into a blender and add gelatine.
Add remainder of ingredients, adding the cottage cheese last.
Blend until smooth.
Fold in pineapple.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Beat eggs and add sugar.
Melt margarine and chocolate together.
Combine mixtures and beat thoroughly.
Add flour, nuts and vanilla.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch metal pan for about 25 minutes at 325°.
Do not overbake.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream together sugar, shortening and eggs.
Stir in flour, baking soda and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add chips and nuts, distributing evenly.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread #1
directions: Mix together the flour, soda, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves, pecans and raisins; set aside.
Cream the sugar, oil, eggs, pumpkin, vanilla extract and water.
Add the flour mixture until well blended.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: blackberry jam cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and well beaten egg yolks.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk and add alternately with dry ingredients.
Add jam and fold in egg whites.
This makes 3 layers.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.
Servings:
about 12.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water; add strawberries.
Allow to partially set.
Spread on top of cream cheese and chill.
Serves 10.

title: fastnacht kuecheles
directions: Mix about 3 cups flour, yeast, salt and nutmeg together in large bowl.
Heat milk and Crisco together until lukewarm.
Add to dry ingredients and beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Add eggs and lemon juice with more flour and beat 2 minutes.
Stir in enough flour to make a soft dough.
Knead well.
Cover dough and let rise until double in bulk.
Place on breadboard and roll about 1/2-inch thick.
Cut in squares.
Cover.
Heat oil to 375°.
Fry a few at a time.
(Pull edges of dough to make a thinner center before frying.)
Drain on paper towel, then shake in a bag with sugar and cinnamon.
Yield:

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly and chill.
Can be prepared and kept refrigerated several days.

title: blender cheese cake
directions: Mix ingredients in blender until smooth and creamy.
Spray 9-inch pie pan with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: easy hawaiian torte
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Cream margarine or butter.
Gradually add sugar, creaming well.
Add egg, pineapple and vanilla.
Mix well.
Stir in the dry ingredients.
Turn into 9-inch square pan, greased and floured on the bottom.
Combine coconut and brown sugar; sprinkle over batter.
Bake until cake springs back when touched lightly in center.
Serve warm or cold with whipped cream or ice cream.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 9.

title: homemade shake 'n bake chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine flour, paprika, salt, garlic powder, thyme and pepper in a plastic bag.
Dip chicken legs and thighs in milk; shake off excess.
Add to bag; shake to coat evenly.
Place chicken on a greased baking sheet.
Bake for 40 minutes, until chicken is tender and coating crisp.
Serves 4.

title: banana-nut bread
directions: Cream together sugar and butter.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Pour into loaf pans.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour or until done.
Makes 4 loaves.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar and water and bring to a boil. Boil slowly for 3 1/2 minutes.
Remove from fire and stir in Marshmallow Creme, peanut butter and vanilla. Stir until all is mixed well.
Pour into buttered pan.

title: broccoli-noodle soup
directions: In a large kettle, heat oil and add onions.
Cook 3 minutes. Add water and bouillon cubes and heat until cubes are dissolved. Add noodles and salt.
Cook 3 minutes.
Add thawed broccoli and garlic powder.
Cook 4 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add milk and cheese and stir until cheese is melted.
Add pepper to taste. Serves 8 to 10.
Stores and reheats well.
Thickens upon standing.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple juice; save juice for later.
Mix all fruit together in a bowl.
Add 1 box of vanilla instant pudding with the pineapple juice, then stir in fruit.
Also, stir in 3 tablespoons of Tang instant drink mix.
Cut up bananas and add to fruit.

title: christmas fruit cookies
directions: Mix sugar, butter and
eggs
thoroughly,
then
stir in buttermilk.
Sift dry ingredients
together and add to creamed mixture.
Stir in fruit and nuts.
Chill
at
least
1 hour or overnight.
Drop with teaspoon about 2 inches apart on greased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes in 375° oven.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix all together.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Fry.
Add cream. Simmer slowly for 30 minutes.
Cover and bake in oven for 40 minutes at 325°.

title: stuffed baked tomatoes
directions: Slice thin layer of each tomato from bottom; core tomatoes, leaving approximately 1/2 inch thickness of tomato.
Saute onion, bell pepper and garlic in butter until onion is translucent.
Pack tomatoes with stuffing mix, onion, pepper, garlic and 1/2 cup of remaining tomato pulp.
Place packed tomatoes in baking dish; sprinkle generously with Parmesan cheese and bake, uncovered, for 40 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: meat loaf
directions: Have meat ground only once in a food chopper with a coarse blade.
Combine meats thoroughly in a large mixing bowl.
Beat eggs well.
Add onion and other seasonings and mix well.
Add to meat and stir or knead until blended.
Pack into an oiled glass 10 x 5 1/4 x 3 1/2-inch bread loaf pan and unmold onto a flat baking pan.
Bake in a moderate oven (350°) for 1 1/2 hours or until well done.
Makes 10 servings.

title: coconut bars
directions: Have butter at room temperature.
Beat first 3 ingredients at No. 3 speed until well blended.
Press firmly into prepared pan. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes. Do not brown.
Beat next 6 ingredients on No. 8 speed about 2 minutes.
Add nuts. Spread over partially baked batter. Sprinkle with coconut.
Bake at 325° about 25 minutes.
Cut into bars while warm.
Cool in pan.
Makes 2 dozen cookies.

title: hot chicken loaf
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients, then add the chicken.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: light style chicken mexicana
directions: Sprinkle chicken with garlic salt.
Heat margarine in skillet. Add chicken; cook 5 minutes.
Turn chicken over.
Add onions and green pepper around edges of chicken.
Cook 5 minutes.
Place rice on serving platter.
Remove chicken from skillet and place over rice; keep warm.
Add Pace and cheese to skillet.
Cook and stir until cheese is melted and sauce is hot.
Pour over chicken and rice; sprinkle with cilantro.
Serve with additional Pace.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients.
Add 2 cups warm water.
Let set for 72 hours, then start feeding.

title: beef in beer
directions: Mix
first
three
ingredients
and
pour
over
beef. Simmer, covered for 3 to 4 hours.
Serve with sauce over small potatoes or hot noodles.
And of course, it's always good with rice too!

title: spinach dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Serve with assorted vegetables or with chips.
Makes 3 1/2 cups.

title: play dough
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mix sticks together.
Add food coloring until desired color.
Put into empty clean coffee cans or wrap in foil. Refrigerate between uses.
Have fun!

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Mix with mayonnaise, water and vanilla.
Bake at 350° until done.
(Test with a toothpick.)

title: combination baked beans
directions: Drain beans and put into large casserole dish.
Fry bacon. Drain.
Add onions, sugar, ketchup, mustard, vinegar and meat. Pour over beans and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: millionaires
directions: Melt caramels with milk over low heat. Add pecans and stir. Drop by teaspoons on buttered Saran Wrap.
Chill in refrigerator on cookie sheet about 1 hour (until hard).
Melt shortening and morsels in saucepan over low heat. Dip candy in chocolate.
Place on plastic wrap. Chill.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer ingredients in order and use desired salad dressing.

title: crawfish jambalaya
directions: Melt butter and add flour.
Brown a little bit.
Add onions and simmer until soft; add fat from crawfish.
Simmer a few more minutes and then add tails, parsley, onion tops and seasonings. Cook 15 minutes.
When ready to serve, add cooked rice.

title: summer squash medley
directions: Melt butter in 3-quart saucepan.
Add celery and onions; cover tightly and simmer 10 to 12 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Peel squash if skin cannot be easily pierced; split and scoop out seeds and fiber.
Dice.
There should be about 5 cups.
Combine with celery and onions; add salt and water.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes or until tender.
Add pepper and serve hot with paprika on top.
Makes 5 servings.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: In a medium bowl cream sugar and oil, add egg and beat by hand well.
In separate bowl sift flour, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Add sifted items to creamed mixture.
Add nutmeats, cold coffee and apples.
Stir well.
Pour into lightly greased and floured cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until done when tested.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Use a 13 x 9-inch cookie pan.
Mix cake mix, soft butter, egg and nuts with a mixer.
Spread in pan; do not grease.

title: manicotti
directions: Cook noodles following label directions; lift with slotted spoon.
Place in bowl of cold water until ready to use.

title: pork chop supreme
directions: Spread mustard on 6 to 8 pork chops. Brown in skillet.
Put in baking dish.
Pour 2 cups chicken noodle soup over top.
Put foil over dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: picante sauce
directions: Cook all ingredients in large pan until tender.
Blend to desired consistency.
Cook 15 minutes.
Add red food coloring, if desired.
Pour into sterilized jars and seal.
Makes 3 quarts.

title: cheese ball
directions: Grate cheeses and mix all ingredients together. Form into a ball and roll in chopped dried beef.

title: cucumber sauce
directions: Peel and grate a large cucumber (discard seeds) and mix with all ingredients.
Chill before serving.

title: sweet n sour meatballs
directions: Combine first seven ingredients; form into 40 bite-size meatballs, using a full teaspoon for each.
Brown meatballs lightly in oil.
Cover; simmer 10 minutes.
Drain excess fat.

title: coconut cake frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place
in
airtight container and leave in refrigerator 2 days
before using it.
Spread between layers, on top and sides and add extra coconut on top.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender; save broth.
Debone chicken and cut up.
Melt margarine and mix with dressing.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan. Put a layer of dressing, chicken and mushroom soup, diluted with 1 can broth.
Top with dressing.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or brown.

title: candy balls
directions: Melt margarine.
Add sugar and milk; mix well.
Add nuts and coconut.
Put in refrigerator; let set overnight.
Shape into balls; place in refrigerator until cool.
Melt chocolate morsels and wax in a double boiler.
Dip balls into mixture until well covered.
Place balls on wax paper to cool.
Keep refrigerated.

title: beet pickle
directions: Add cooked sliced beets and bring to a boil.
Put into hot sterilized jars and seal.

title: pepper relish
directions: Take peppers and put in pot.
Add pickling salt, not iodized salt.
Let sit for 2 hours.
Add vinegar and 2 cups of salt.
Stir and cook on the stove for 45 minutes to an hour.
Get it thick but not dry.
It is ready to refrigerate or preserve.
Keep a cover on it to keep the heat in.

title: pittsburgh potatoes
directions: Mix all together.
Save 1/2 of Velveeta for top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in boiling water for 5 minutes; drain. Combine soup, sour cream and boned, canned chicken.
Stir in carrots.
Fold in squash and onion.
Combine stuffing mix and butter.
Spread half of stuffing mixture in bottom of a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spoon vegetable and chicken mixture on top. Sprinkle remaining stuffing mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: friday night pizza
directions: Place 1 cup of milk in microwave for 3 minutes. Add ice water. Put in freezer to cool. Mix flour, sugar, salt and yeast. (You can use your bread maker, a Kitchen Aid mixer or just a wooden spoon and your hands to mix the dough.) Once the milk/water mixture is cool enough, add gradually to the dough. Knead very thoroughly. Let rise in a warm place for 1 hour. Grease a cookie sheet or a pizza pan. Roll out the dough on a floured surface. Form a pizza crust with your hands by tossing it while stretching the dough. Stretch to fit your pizza pan or a large cookie sheet. Make sauce after you've formed your crust on your pan.

title: boned chicken breasts
directions: Sprinkle breasts with salt and pepper.
Roll a strip of bacon around each breast.
In bottom of pan, spread out dried beef, enough to cover the bottom.
Place breasts on top of beef.
In a separate bowl, mix 1 can of cream of mushroom soup and carton of sour cream.
Spoon over breasts.
Cover tightly
with foil.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.
Remove foil and cook 30 minutes longer.

title: pork chops in wine
directions: Mash butter, mustard, salt and pepper to taste and spread on both sides of pork chops.
Brown onion in salad oil and then add pork chops; cook until brown.
Pour wine over chops and simmer 1 hour. Sprinkle with parsley.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix jello, using 1 cup of boiling water and 1 cup of saved orange juice and cranberry juice.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour in glass dish.
Chill overnight.
Makes a beautiful Christmas dish.

title: dill pickles
directions: Make a	brine
of 1/2 cup of salt to 1 gallon of water. Pour over
whole
cucumbers
(leave a little stem on them) and soak overnight.	Pack
in
sterilized jars with a head of dill in the bottom and a head
of
dill on the top.
Add a pinch of alum the size of a
bean.
Grape
or
cherry
leaves make them greener. Bring to a boil
2 quarts water, 1 quart vinegar and 1 cup salt. Pour over
cucumbers
and
seal.
(For 1 quart of pickles, use 1 cup water, 1/2 cup vinegar and 2 tablespoons of salt.) May process in	boiling
water	bath for 20 minutes for quarts and 10 minutes for pints.	(I don't usually do this.)

title: dip for fruit no. 2
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add chopped walnuts, pecans or almonds.
Serve with sliced apples, pears, etc.

title: chocolate sheath cake
directions: Stir sugar and flour together in a large mixing bowl.
In a large saucepan, bring to a boil the margarine, water and cocoa. Pour over dry ingredients and stir.
Add eggs, buttermilk, soda and vanilla.
Bake in 11 x 17-inch pan for 20 minutes at 400°.

title: garbanzo bean salad
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients in a large bowl and stir well. Add remaining ingredients and stir gently.
Serve and chill or serve at room temperature.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix 12 ounces Cool Whip (save remaining Cool Whip) with all other ingredients (except nuts) in mixing bowl.
Place mixture in 2 graham cracker crusts.
Top with remaining Cool Whip and nut sprinkles.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream margarine and Crisco with 1 1/2 cups sugar and eggs. Sift together flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt.
Blend the flour mixture into the creamed mixture.
Shape rounded teaspoonfuls of dough into balls.
Blend together cinnamon and 3 tablespoons of sugar.
Roll cookie dough balls in cinnamon and sugar and place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes or until golden on top.
Cool on racks.
Yields about 6 dozen.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: In large saucepan, combine tomatoes, onion, celery, tomato sauce, water and 1 teaspoon salt and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, cut tops off green peppers and remove seeds; set aside.
In a bowl, combine ground beef, rice, basil and salt; mix well.
Fill peppers with beef mixture.
Place peppers in tomato sauce.
Spoon some sauce over tops of peppers.
Cover and simmer for 40 to 45 minutes until beef is cooked and peppers are tender.
Yields 4 servings.

title: tortilla chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wash chicken and pat dry.
Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Wrap in foil and bake for 1 hour or until tender, reserve juice.

title: snappy barbecue beef
directions: Put meat in a roasting pan. Mix all ingredients in a bowl and then cover the meat with them. Bake at 350° in covered roasting pan for approximately 5 hours. While cooking, shred with a fork several times. Serve on a bed of rice with a dinner roll, or make as a sandwich on a hoagie roll.

title: caramel pie
directions: Brown coconut and pecans in butter until lightly brown (be careful not to burn it).
Cream the Eagle Brand and cream cheese until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour 1/4 of the filling into each pie shell.

Then sprinkle with coconut pecan mixture and drizzle with warm caramel (take lid off and warm in microwave). Pour rest of filling into each pie shell and sprinkle with rest of pecan-coconut mixture and top with caramel.

title: pear cake
directions: Use creaming method by hand; add pears last.
Optional: add 1 cup chopped pecans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes in a tube pan.

title: seafood pasta
directions: In large skillet over medium heat, melt butter and saute garlic, mushrooms and minced parsley until tender.
Add seafood, cook 3 to 5 minutes or until shrimp turns pink, stirring frequently.
Add tomato sauce and macaroni.
Heat through.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Mound pasta mixture on serving dish; sprinkle with cheese.

title: noodles
directions: Add softened shortening and water to beaten eggs.
Add baking powder; beat well.
Add flour to make dough that is stiff, but easily handled.
Divide into 3 rounds.
Roll out on floured board until thin, let dry slightly, then cut into long strips.
Place strips on top of each other and cut into noodles.
Place on large surface and dry.
Can be frozen in plastic bags.
Cook in rich boiling broth.

title: betty's pecan pies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Brown pie shells. Beat eggs, melt butter, and chop pecans. Mix all ingredients together and pour in pie shells. Cook in oven until done.

title: energy bars
directions: Melt margarine.
Add marshmallows and melt.
Add peanut butter; stir until melted.
Mix raisins, oatmeal and Rice Krispies; add and mix well.
Put in a greased 11 x 13-inch pan. Top with sesame seed.
Let stay overnight.
Cut into serving pieces.

title: barbecued hamburger
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together in order given.
When milk is absorbed, wet tips of fingers and shape into balls. Brown on both sides in about 5 tablespoons hot fat and cook slowly 10 minutes.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Add to meat in skillet and cook slowly for 20 minutes, turning occasionally.

title: thin layer chocolate cake
directions: Mix according to directions, put 3/4 cup in 9-inch cake pan and bake (14 layers).

title: homemade strawberry ice cream
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and cream until sugar is melted.
Add half and half and whipping cream.
Fold in thawed strawberries. Pour into freezer can and add enough whole milk to fill to 1 inch from top.
Freeze.

title: low cholesterol barbecue sauce
directions: Combine ingredients and add cooked lean meat.
Simmer for 20 minutes after bringing to a boil.
Makes 4 servings with 83 mg cholesterol per serving.

title: i've got a secret cake
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla.
Mix flour, cinnamon, soda and salt.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Then add in order, cottage cheese,
beets,
pineapple,
coconut and nuts.
Mixing well
after each
addition.
Then beat 1 minute.
Pour in well greased cake pan.
Bake
at
for 45 to 55 minutes.
Cake gets
very brown
so
check center with toothpick.
Then cool. Then ice with a cream cheese frosting.

title: corn casserole
directions: Prepare rice according to package directions, add butter and stir until melted, then add corn and soup. Stir in cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, remove from oven and sprinkle some cheese on top and paprika for color. Add more cheese if you like.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine sugars, pumpkin, oil and eggs.
Beat until well blended.
Sift together flour, salt, soda, nutmeg, cinnamon and ginger.
Add flour mixture to sugar mixture and mix well.
Stir in raisins, nuts and water.
Spoon into well-oiled 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 65 to 75 minutes or until done when tested.
Cool on rack.

title: alabama biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Mix in other ingredients.
Stir well.
Put on floured board.
Knead a little, keeping dough as soft as possible.
Cut out biscuits.
Dip both sides of biscuits in melted butter. Put in greased pan.
Let rise for 1 hour. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: venison steak
directions: Trim all fat from steaks. Cut into 3-inch squares. Using a mallet, pound flour into both sides of steaks. Melt shortening in large skillet and brown meat slowly (15 to 20 minutes). Season to taste with salt and pepper. Transfer browned pieces to a 2 to 3-quart dish. Pour 2 cans of mushroom soup and add enough water to cover all pieces. Cover and bake until tender (approximately 2 1/2 hours) in a 350° oven. Add additional water if necessary.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Debone and cool.
Mix up dumplings according to recipe on the Bisquick box.
Put in chicken broth, one spoonful at a time.
Add deboned chicken meat and cover; cook 10 minutes on medium heat.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: burger biscuits
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onions.
Stir constantly to scramble meat. Drain and cool.
Add soup
and mix well to make thick mixture.

title: chicken rice surprise
directions: Boil chicken breast until done.
Cut into bite size pieces. Add rest of ingredients to chicken and water except rice.
Bring to a boil.
Add rice; remove from burner.
Cover.
Let stand until water is absorbed by rice.
Feeds 6 to 8 people.
Lip smackin' good.
Low-fat.

title: jack jarr potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes 1 hour at 400°.
Cut top lengthwise; scoop out potatoes.
Put in mixing bowl with butter and a little salt and pepper.
Fry bacon until crisp.
Beat potatoes and butter until smooth.
Add onion, sour cream and bacon (crumbled).
Put potatoes back into skins; sprinkle with a little paprika.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4.

title: low-fat chicken, vegetables and rice
directions: Boil chicken and broth for 15 to 20 minutes, drain and keep liquid.
Cook oil, garlic and mushrooms in large skillet and add chicken.
Cook about 2 minutes.
Add broth, frozen vegetables and salt and pepper to mixture.
Bring to a boil.
Add rice and let simmer for 5 minutes.

title: low sodium bread
directions: Mix oil and sugar.
Add water and sprinkle yeast in and stir well.
Add	1 egg and enough flour for thick batter.
Let rise. Add more
flour
and
knead
to
make
into 2 loaves or rolls. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit casserole
directions: Melt 1/2 butter in 8 x 11 x 2-inch Pyrex dish.
Drain fruit and put in dish.
Drizzle cranberry juice over fruit.
Cover with brown sugar.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers.
Dot with remaining 1/2 butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sourdough bread starter
directions: Mix warm water, sugar and potato flakes for "feed" and add to starter.
Allow starter to stand out of refrigerator all day.
This does not rise, just bubbles.
At the end of the day (12 hours), take out 1 cup to use in making bread.
Return remaining starter to refrigerator.
Keep 3 to 5 days; feed again and make bread.
If not making bread, give 1 cup of starter away or throw away.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Melt butter in casserole dish and set aside.
Tear bread into cubes and toss in melted butter until each piece is coated.
Set aside.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter in a large iron skillet.
Spread brown sugar over first, then arrange pineapple.
Place cherry in center of each slice.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat egg yolks until light.
Add sugar gradually.
Add pineapple juice and flour.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in a moderate 375° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Turn cake onto plate while hot.

title: sour cream for baked potatoes
directions: Mix and refrigerate 1 hour before using.
Will keep a week or more.

title: turtle dessert
directions: Finely crush vanilla wafers. Add melted butter. Press into 9 x 13-inch baking pan or casserole. Top with chocolate chips and pecans. Drizzle with caramel topping. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes. Chill and slice.

title: chocolate marshmallow fudge
directions: Mix sugar and evaporated milk in heavy saucepan.
Cook until it boils, stirring constantly.
Cook 10 minutes longer, still stirring.
In a large bowl, mix chocolate chips, marshmallows and butter (chopped up in 1-inch pieces) and nuts.
Add cooked mixture into other ingredients.
Stir vigorously until it becomes thick. Dump into ungreased cake pan.
Cut into squares when cooled.

title: lentil soup
directions: Soak lentils for at least 2 hours.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Put all ingredients in a large pot with water to cover, and cook at least 1 hour or until vegetables and meat are tender.

title: no weep meringue(like pie shops)
directions: In a saucepan, cook cornstarch, sugar and 1/2 cup water until thick.
Cool and add 3 unbeaten egg whites.
Beat until satiny and in peaks.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: apple danish cheesecake
directions: In small bowl, combine cracker crumbs and sugar.
Stir in butter.
Press into bottom and up sides of a greased spring form pan.
Set aside.

title: lemon broccoli chicken
directions: In skillet in hot oil, cook chicken 10 minutes or until brown on both sides. Combine soup, milk, lemon juice and pepper. Pour over chicken. Top each breast with lemon slices. Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 5 minutes or until chicken is fork-tender. Stir occasionally. Makes 4 servings.

title: onion pie
directions: Combine crumbs and melted butter.
Press into an 8-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Saute onions in oil until tender; arrange into pie shell.
Mix eggs, milk, salt and pepper; pour over onions.
Top with Cheddar.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lemon bread
directions: Wrap immediately in foil.
Refrigerate while hot.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: almost-no-sugar added popsicles
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add frozen orange juice and the cold water.
Freeze in store bought popsicle containers, an ice cube tray or small paper cups.
If using ice cube trays or paper cups, place a stick in when partially frozen.
Good on hot days.
Jell-O delays drippings.
Other flavored jello and frozen juices can be substituted as well.
Makes 16 to 24 popsicles depending on size.

title: crispy baked potato fingers
directions: In a small bowl, combine sour cream and 1 tablespoon of the seasoning.
Cover and chill until serving time.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Scrub potatoes; pat dry.
Cut each lengthwise to make 8 wedges.
In a small saucepan, melt butter or margarine.
Stir in remaining seasoning.
Dip potato wedges in butter or margarine mixture, turning to coat on all sides.
Arrange wedges in a single layer on a baking sheet cut side down.
Spoon any leftover mixture over potatoes.
Bake 30 minutes.
Turn wedges over and continue baking 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown and edges are crisp. Drain on paper towels.
Serve with sour cream dip.

title: claire's ground beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and add the other ingredients.
Cover and bake at 325° for 1/2 hour.

title: almond coleslaw
directions: Combine all ingredients, except mayo, cream and almonds. Chill.
Just before serving, blend mayo and cream.
Toss dressing and almonds with salad.

title: chili
directions: Cook meat and onion until lightly browned. Stir in remaining ingredients. Cover and simmer for 1 hour.

title: deep fried bananas
directions: Mix together flour, sugar and baking powder.
Whisk together milk, vanilla and eggs.
Cut bananas 3/4-inch thick.
Mix dry ingredients with wet ingredients together.
Dip bananas, then deep-fry until golden brown.

title: cherry peek
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, beating in between each. Add vanilla and flour. Spread 3/4 of the batter in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spoon pie filling evenly over batter. Drop remaining batter by spoonfuls on cherry filling. Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: fudge
directions: In a heavy pot, over low heat, melt the semi-sweet chocolate chips with the sweetened condensed milk.
When melted, remove pot from heat.
Add vanilla and chopped nuts, stirring well.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch pan.
Refrigerate for 2 hours until firm.

title: chicken wings
directions: Note:
If you wish to 1 1/2 times the recipe, just add 5 more wings; if double amount all ingredients must be doubled.

title: choco-peanut toppers
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients and mix well. Drop by level teaspoon onto greased cookie sheets.
Flatten to 1/4-inch with a glass, greased on the bottom, then dipped in sugar.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Spread warm cookies with Peanut Butter Topping.
Drizzle with Chocolate Glaze.
Let stand until glaze is set.
Makes 54 to 60 cookies.

title: old fashioned coconut icing
directions: Cook milk and sugar together until thick. Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla. Beat together until creamy. Pour over cake and sprinkle with flake coconut.

title: ol' fashion apple crisp
directions: Using prepared apples, mix flour, sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and orange juice.
Pour over apples, coating evenly.
Put in baking dish and dot with butter.

title: tasty turkey chili(low-fat)
directions: Saute onion, garlic and green pepper in olive oil.
Brown turkey.
Add Chili-O mix, tomatoes, drained kidney beans and water.
Bring to a boil; simmer about 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: fun in the sun
directions: Prepare pudding with the 2 cups milk as directed.
Spoon into crusts.
Shortly before serving, put jellybean sunglasses in place.
Cut a curved piece of licorice for mouth and put in place. Put candy corn points facing out around face.
Great summertime dessert.
Serves 6.

title: sloppy joes
directions: In large pan, brown beef.
Add onions and green pepper and cook until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 10 minutes.
Serve over toasted buns.

title: lazy daisy cake
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, then flour, baking powder and salt. Heat 1/2 cup milk and 2 tablespoons butter.
Cool.
Mix all together.
Bake in greased pan.

title: blue ribbon pumpkin pie
directions: Combine pumpkin, sugar, spices and flour in a bowl.
Add eggs; mix well, then add milk and vanilla.
Mix well and pour in unbaked pie shell.
Makes 2 pies.

title: mary woods sin cake
directions: Mix ingredients; press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°.
Let cool.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix sour cream and brown sugar well and then fold in
Cool Whip.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Sift flour in bowl and set aside.
Separate eggs; place whites in small mixing bowl and beat (use mixer) with 1/4 cup sugar at high speed and set aside.
Put butter, shortening and 2 3/4 cups sugar in large bowl and beat at medium speed.
Add egg yolks one at a time.
Add flour and sour cream alternately.
Add baking soda, vanilla and lemon extract.
Add egg whites with mixer on low speed.
Bake at 300° in greased pan (10-inch tube) for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together and set aside.
Beat eggs and vanilla until frothy.
Add pumpkin, carrots and raisins.
Mix dry ingredients into pumpkin mixture.
Spray muffin tin with Pam and divide mixture to make 12 muffins.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown beef, onion and pepper in skillet.
Drain fat.
Add other ingredients.
Bake in casserole dish for 1 hour at 350°.

title: biehl sugar cookies
directions: Combine the ingredients in their order.
Add white flour until thick like pie dough.
Roll out on floured board and cut shapes as desired.
After first 2 or 3 rollings, the dough will be less tasty so plan to use as much dough in each rolling as possible. Thick cookies have a cake-like taste.

title: peach bread
directions: Drain peaches, reserving 1/4 cup syrup.
Finely chop 1 cup peaches; set aside.
In blender, combine remaining peaches, margarine, eggs, syrup and lemon juice.
Cover; blend until smooth.
Stir together dry ingredients.
Add egg mixture; stir until moistened.
Fold in reserved peaches.
Turn into greased 8 x 4 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: linda twelves' buffalo wings
directions: Season chicken wings with salt, pepper and Tony Chachere seasoning (to suit your taste).
Fry wings in oil.
Make sauce of butter, hot sauce, garlic and vinegar.
Pour over chicken and let soak in.

title: broccoli with cheese
directions: Heat 1-inch salted water (1/2 teaspoon salt to 1 cup water). To boil, add broccoli.
Cover and heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and boil until stems are tender, 12 to 15 minutes.
Drain.

title: peanut butter oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix in order given, mixing soda with oatmeal.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° until done, 10 to 12 minutes.
(Batter will be very stiff.)

title: strawberry cooler
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, sugar and water.
Pour into ice cube tray.
Put 1 whole strawberry in each cube.
Freeze cubes.
To serve, put several cubes in each glass.
Fill glass with carbonated beverage. Yields 6 servings.

title: sancho beans
directions: Place all ingredients in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken dinner in a dish
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 12 x 8-inch (2 quart) baking dish, arrange chicken, potatoes, carrots and onion.
Pour chicken broth over preceding mix.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover with foil.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Let stand overnight.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix together dried apples and sugar.
Set aside.
Mix together oil, nuts, eggs and vanilla.
Sift together salt, flour, soda and cinnamon.
Put all mixtures together and mix well.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: strawberry jack daniels margarita(this ain't no sipping tea, ladies)
directions: In blender container, prepare margarita mix according to directions, substituting Jack Daniels for tequila.
Add remaining ingredients.
Blend well, adding ice until desired consistency is reached.

title: miniature cheesecakes
directions: You will also need 24 cupcake liners.
Line cupcake pans with liners.
Place a vanilla wafer in the bottom of each liner.

title: rolled shrimp sandwich
directions: Mix ingredients using enough mayonnaise to give good spreading consistency.
Cut crust from day old thin bread spread with shrimp mixture.
Roll tightly in a slightly dampened towel. Chill. Slice into approximately 1/4-inch slices.
Yellow and/or red food coloring may be used to accentuate colors in these sandwiches.

title: more
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet and season with salt and pepper. At same time, boil 2-quarts water (approximately) and 1 teaspoon salt.
When water comes to a boil, add noodles and boil for 10 minutes.
Drain noodles.
Add hamburger, corn and soup; mix up thoroughly.
Heat until warm throughout.
Add Cheddar cheese as desired.

title: tex mex dip
directions: Spread beans in large pie plate or quiche pan.
Mix avocado, lemon juice, salt and pepper (a potato masher works well).
Spread over beans.
Combine sour cream, mayo and taco mix; spread over avocado layer.
Top with tomatoes, shredded cheese and black olives.
Serve chilled with tortilla chips.

title: pozole #2
directions: In a big pot, put chicken and water; enough to cover the chicken. Add half of the onion and garlic. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to medium and continue to cook until halfway cooked. Add hominy and continue cooking until both chicken and hominy are tender.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix crab meat, green peppers, salt, pepper, parsley and mustard.
Combine egg and mayonnaise and add to above.
Mix in cracker crumbs and Worcestershire.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Make into cakes and fry in 1/2-inch oil (350°) about 4 minutes on each side.
Drain.

title: marinated green beans
directions: Put green beans, sliced mushrooms and quartered artichoke hearts in large bowl.
Sprinkle generously with McCormick salad seasoning.
Pour prepared Italian dressing over vegetables. Marinate 24 hours.
Just before serving, place sliced tomatoes on top of dish.
Enjoy!

title: party potatoes
directions: In a large bowl, combine potatoes, sour cream, cream cheese, chives and garlic powder.
Put in a 2-quart casserole dish. Combine bread crumbs with butter; sprinkle over potato mixture. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Top with cheese.
Serve immediately.
Can be made the day ahead and baked the next day.

title: duckling
directions: Split duck down
back.	Sprinkle
with 1 teaspoon salt. Heat fat in
large
skillet,
add duck.	Cook until browned at 300°. Mix orange	juice,	hot
sauce,
allspice and remaining salt, pour over
duck.
Cook
covered	over
low heat, turning duck several times
for	about 45 minutes.
Add oranges.
Cook 15 minutes longer or until duck is tender.

title: hershey's cocoa fudge
directions: Combine dry ingredients and milk, bring to a boil on medium heat, let boil without stirring until softball stage.
Add vanilla and butter, let cool until 110 degrees and stir until thick.

title: lentil-pepperoni soup
directions: Rinse lentils.
In Dutch oven, combine with 6 cups water, pepperoni, onion, salt, oregano, sage and cayenne pepper.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add tomatoes, carrot and celery.
Cover and simmer 40 minutes longer.
Meanwhile, cook bulgur or brown rice according to package directions.
Add to soup and serve.

title: sweet potato crunch
directions: Mash potatoes slightly; add other ingredients; pour into a 12x8x2 inch pan; bake at 400 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Put in ungreased loaf pan, 9 x 5 x 3-inch.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar together until fluffy; add next 4 ingredients.
Sprinkle pecans on bottom of pie shell.
Pour the filling over pecans.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 35 minutes longer (outer edge of filling should be set).
Knife inserted in center should come out clean.

title: summer surprise
directions: Combine margarine with vanilla wafers.
Reserve couple of tablespoonfuls for garnish.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Put in loaf pan.
Shape lightly with barbecue sauce.
Cover with foil; cook 1 1/2 hours.
When done, take foil off.
Let brown 15 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Pour off grease.
Bake at 350°.

title: garlic lover's noodles
directions: Boil noodles in saucepan on low-medium heat.
Saute garlic, oil and basil until garlic is soft (not browned).
Place drained noodles in serving dish.
Pour garlic mixture over noodles; mix thoroughly, sprinkling Parmesan cheese according to taste.
Serve. Makes 4 servings.

title: stuffin good pork chops
directions: Cook onion and celery in margarine in medium size saucepan, until tender.
Add water, bring to boil.
Remove from heat and add croutons all at one time, tossing slightly until evenly moistened. Cut pocket in each chop from bone side.
Fill with crouton mixture.
Place stuffed chops, flat side down, in a shallow baking pan.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour or until chops are browned and tender.

title: baked carrots
directions: Slice carrots in long strips.
Place in shallow casserole dish and sprinkle with onion and sugar.
Salt and pepper to taste. Pour water over.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 10 (3 ounce) servings with 53 calories and 2 g fat.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix together first four ingredients.
Roll into balls.
In top of double boiler, mix wax and chips together.
Leave over hot water and dip balls in mixture, one at a time.
Place on wax paper to cool.

title: chocolate bread
directions: Pour the warm water into a large bowl.
Sprinkle the yeast over the top and let stand until the yeast dissolves, about 1 minute.
Whisk in sugar, and salt.
Whisk in the eggs and butter until well mixed.
Using a wooden spoon, beat in the cocoa and then the flour to make soft dough.

title: spinach dip
directions: Take uncooked spinach.
Squeeze, dry and combine with all remaining ingredients.
Chill and serve.

title: de-lite-fully yours
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water. Stir in buttermilk and pineapple. Chill until firm.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add syrup and salt.
Beat well.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Add pecans.
Pour into pie shell and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: make-ahead mashed potatoes
directions: Cook and mash potatoes (do not add milk).
Then beat all ingredients together with a hand mixer.
Place in a buttered casserole dish and add more butter on the top.
Cover and place in refrigerator overnight.
Bake next day in oven at 350°, covered, for 1/2 hour or longer, if needed.

title: poor man's dinner
directions: Brown hamburger.
Mix with pork and beans and brown sugar. Heat and serve.

title: christmas punch(or anytime punch)
directions: Pour cranberry juice into saucepan and add sugar.
Heat just enough to dissolve sugar.
Remove from heat.
Mix with nectar and pineapple juice.
Refrigerate.
Add ginger ale just prior to serving.
Red food coloring may be added.

title: red pepper dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Serve with crackers or fresh veggies.

title: mexican corn
directions: Make rice like directions on box.
Melt Cheez Whiz.
Mix ingredients.
Grate Cheddar cheese over top.
Bake at 350° until cheese is crispy.

title: potato doughnuts
directions: Beat eggs with sugar and vanilla until light.
Add potatoes and oil.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add alternately with milk to potato mixture, beating well.
Chill dough 3 hours.
Fry in deep, hot fat (375°) for 1 minute on each side.
Drain.
Dip in sugar. Makes about 2 to 2 1/2 dozen.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat with chopped onion. Drain grease from hamburger and onion; mix with sauces and simmer 2 hours. Layer meat and sauce with egg noodles. Top with Mozzarella cheese. Cover with slices of pepperoni. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sauerkraut
directions: Add onion, celery, carrot and green pepper to well drained sauerkraut.
Add sugar to oil and vinegar and stir well until blended.
Add this mixture to sauerkraut mixture and mix well. Store, covered, overnight.
Very good.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Soak oatmeal in hot water.
Combine next 3 ingredients.
Blend all these together.
Add eggs.
Stir in last 4 ingredients.
Stir well.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: scotch shortbread cookies
directions: Mix well together until it's like putty.
Make into rolls and refrigerate until firm.
Cut in 1/4-inch slices.
Cook at 325° to 350° for 7 to 12 minutes.

title: scalloped eggplant
directions: Pare the eggplant and cut into small even pieces.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter in a skillet.
Add the green pepper and onion. Cook for a few minutes.
Add the tomatoes, eggplant, salt and pepper. Cook for 10 minutes.
Place the mixture in a shallow greased baking dish.
Melt the remaining butter in a skillet and stir in the bread crumbs.
Sprinkle the crumb mixture over the eggplant. Bake in 350 degree oven for 15 minutes or until the eggplant is tender and crumbs are brown. May top with cheese if desired.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix and bake at 375° for approximately 15 minutes.
As you mix, add a little flour if the dough seems sticky.
I pat the biscuits out, but you can also roll them out and cut them.
Makes 12 to 15 biscuits.

title: homemade macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Boil noodles until barely tender; drain. Pour noodles into large casserole pan. Add 1/2 of cheeses and pepper. Stir. Mix eggs, milk, water and salt; pour over mixture. Top with rest of cheeses and pats of butter. Bake for 45 minutes or until bubbly.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, salt and cocoa; sift.
Add eggs, one at a time, and mix well.
Stir in vanilla, milk, margarine, coconut and pecans.
Pour in 2 deep-dish pie shells or 3 shallow pie shells. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown and firm when you shake.

title: nutty fingers
directions: Mix in order.
Roll in shape of fingers.
Bake at 350° until light brown.
Roll in 4x sugar while warm.

title: humdingers
directions: Combine margarine, sugar and dates in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cereal, walnuts, vanilla and sesame seed.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in confectioners sugar.
Let stand until cool.
Store in airtight container.
Yield:
36 servings.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in butter.
Mix all other ingredients together (except sour cream and cheese).
Add onions and pepper.
Top with sour cream and grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: brownie pudding
directions: Sift together the flour, sugar, cocoa, baking powder and salt. Add milk, oil and vanilla.
Mix until smooth.
Stir in nuts. Pour into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch square pan.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Combine the first 5 ingredients; cut in shortening.
Add buttermilk; mix well.
Add yeast.
Blend on floured board.
Store in covered container in refrigerator.
Take out amount needed; roll 1/2-inch thick.
Cut out biscuits; dip in melted butter.
Bake at 400° for about 15 minutes.

title: everyday meat  loaf
directions: Soak bread crumbs in milk; add meat, eggs, onion and seasonings.
Mix well; form in individual loaves and place in greased muffin pans.
Cover meat loaves with Piquant Sauce.
Bake in 350° oven 45 minutes.
Serves 8 people or form in single loaf in 4 3/4 x 8 3/4-inch loaf pan; spread over with sauce and bake one hour.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding milk to make a firm consistency. Fry in an iron skillet with just enough oil to float the fritters. Makes 4 to 6 fritters.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar and Karo together.
Add beaten whole eggs, butter, pecans and vanilla to mixture and blend together.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 325° for about 1 hour.

title: daffodil sunshine cake
directions: Mix first half same as angel food cake and place in bottom of tube pan.
For second half, beat egg yolks and sugar together. Add flour and baking powder alternately with hot water.
Add vanilla.
Pour on top of white and bake at 325° to 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: boiled custard
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Chill to thicken.

title: apricot chicken
directions: Pour over chicken and bake at 350° until done or brown chicken parts on both sides and pour apricot mixture over it.
Simmer until done.

title: olive salad
directions: Combine
all
ingredients and mix well.
Put in jar and let set overnight.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: chili-o cheeseburgers
directions: Combine beef, Chili-O seasoning mix and 2 tablespoons mustard and mix well.
Shape into 6 hamburgers.
In small bowl combine remaining mustard, cheese and chilies.
Broil or grill until done. Top with cheese mixture.
Cook 30 seconds longer or until cheese melts.
Serve on rolls.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Drain liquid off kraut.
Add celery, pepper and onion.
Mix oil, vinegar and sugar; heat until sugar has melted.
Chill.
Pour over kraut; mix and chill.

title: sugar drop cookies
directions: Set oven at 375°.
Put shortening on a piece of waxed paper. Rub over cookie sheets until lightly greased.
Soften shortening with wooden spoon.
Mix sugar in well.
Add egg.
Beat until fluffy.
Add vanilla.
Sift flour onto paper.
Measure.
Add baking powder and salt.
Sift mixture onto another paper.
Add milk to shortening-egg mixture.
Add flour mixture and nuts.

title: onion pie
directions: Use frozen Pillsbury pie crust or your favorite recipe.

title: banana oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Beat well.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: rolled sugar cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar; add egg, milk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Stir flour with baking powder and salt.
Blend into creamed mixture.
Divide in half.
Cover.
Chill 1 hour.
On a lightly floured surface, roll each half to 1/8-inch thickness for thick cookies.
Cut into desired shapes.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: soda irish bread
directions: Knead.
Let rise.
Mark with your knife in center of dough sign of cross.
Bake at 375° until golden brown.

title: cherry topped cheese cakes
directions: Prepare cake mix according to instructions on package. Divide into 2 9x13 greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Beat cream cheese and powdered sugar together until fluffy; fold in cool whip.
Divide evenly over both cakes. Top with pie filling and chill at least 4 hours.

title: days of wine and roses cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix at medium speed for 2 minutes. Pour into a greased and sugared Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Mix sugar and flour; add milk and pour over butter.
Pour peaches and syrup over that; bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: wax bean casserole
directions: Cook wax beans as directions on the package.
Brown the onion in a small amount of vegetable oil over low heat.
Pour browned onions over the wax beans.
Add the bread crumbs and butter; mix thoroughly.
Pour into a casserole dish and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: sour cream chicken enchiladas
directions: In a saucepan, gradually stir chicken broth into flour.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly. Cook and stir 1 minute more. Remove from heat. Stir some of the hot mixture into the sour cream, parsley and pepper.
Return all to hot mixture in saucepan. Set aside.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease the bottom of a 12-cup muffin pan.
Beat egg, milk and oil.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt in a mixing bowl.
Add liquid ingredients to dry ingredients and stir until just moistened.
Fold in blueberries and put in muffin pan.
Bake for 20 minutes or until brown.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mash sweet potatoes.
Whip all other ingredients and mix into potatoes.
Pour into greased casserole.

title: mother's holiday fruit cookies
directions: Mix well the shortening, brown sugar and eggs.
Add sour milk. Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Mix in. Mix in pecans, cherries and dates.
Chill.

title: health bread
directions: Cook raisins and water together 5 minutes and cool.
Mix all together.
Put into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: dump sheet cake
directions: Cook in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish or sheet cake pan. Sprinkle pineapple in pan first.
Layer the fruit evenly all over the pan, then sprinkle cake mix over fruit.
Mix melted margarine and 1/4 cup milk together.
Pour over ingredients.
Top with coconut and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Turn down heat and bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: baked bean delight
directions: Saute
onions
in bacon drippings; combine all ingredients, except
bacon in a greased 1 1/2 quart casserole and mix well. Top with bacon.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: tang salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: kielbasa in polish sauce
directions: Saute onions in 2 tablespoons butter or oleo until golden. Add sausage, bouillon and beer. Simmer 20
minutes.
Blend flour into 1 tablespoon butter or oleo. Stir into broth.
Add vinegar, brown sugar, salt and pepper.
Add potatoes.
Cook over medium heat 10 to 15 minutes.
Slice kielbasa into chunks.
I add this back into potatoes and broth and heat through. (Use beer to your own taste.)

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Fold all ingredients together.
Put in dish and freeze.
Serve partially frozen.
May be refrozen.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Put in unbaked crust and cover with top crust.
Brush pastry with a little cream and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until nice and brown.

title: linguini salad
directions: Cook linguini.
Drain and stir in rest of ingredients.

title: tiramisuitalian, "lift-me-up-cake!"
directions: NOTE:
You MUST take your time with this!!
Beat the egg yolks until they're pale yellow in color, gradually add the 1/2 cup of sugar, beat well until the sugar has dissolved.
Gradually add flour, mix well and set aside.
Beat the egg whites until they stand in firm peaks.
Gradually fold the whites into the yolk mixture.
Put into a piping bag and squirt 2-inch fingers onto a baking tray.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and bake at 350°f. 180°c. gas mark 4 for 10-15 minutes until lightly browned.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Sprinkle salt over cucumbers and onions.
Let stand 1 to 2 hours.
Mix sugar, vinegar and mustard seed in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil. Cool. When completely cold, pour over cucumbers.
Leave out of freezer 2 to 4 hours, then put in containers and freeze.

title: jag
directions: In a large pot, simmer onion in vegetable oil.
Drain beans and add to pot.
Add water, rice, salt, pepper and paprika; bring to a boil.
Stir and cover.
Cook over low flame for 20 minutes. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken in sour cream
directions: Rub chicken with seasonings and place in crock-pot.
Mix wine, soup and mushrooms together and pour over chicken.
Cook on low for 6 to 8 hours or high for 2 to 3 hours.
Remove chicken from crock-pot and add sour cream to sauce.
Stir and heat.
Add chicken to finished sauce.

title: fillets baked in sour cream
directions: Grease 2-quart baking dish with 1 teaspoon oleo.
Arrange fish in baking dish.
Blend salt, Tabasco, paprika and Parmesan cheese into sour cream.
Spread over fish.
Top with bread crumbs and dot with remaining oleo.
Bake uncovered in 350° oven for 30 minutes, until fish is easily flaked with fork.
Serve with lemon.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: apple bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add beaten eggs and buttermilk. Mix soda, salt, cinnamon and flour.
Add to sugar mixture.
Add apples and stir all together with a mixer.
Put in a greased and floured loaf pan.
Top with mixture of 1 teaspoon sugar and 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes.

title: spanish chicken and rice
directions: Brown chicken in olive oil in a Dutch oven.
Remove.
Saute celery and onion.
When nearly soft, add garlic, parsley and tomatoes.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Add rice, peas, broth, saffron and chicken.
Stir well.
Boil, cover, lower heat and simmer gently for about 25 minutes until all liquid is absorbed.

title: more
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add oil.
Brown bell pepper and onion; drain.
Add all other ingredients.
Chop cheese; add to mixture. Save a small amount to grate on top.
Pour into oblong baking dish; cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Grate remaining cheese on top; return to oven until cheese melts.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake using box directions in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool. Cut into bite size pieces.
Make pudding using box directions.
In punch bowl, layer ingredients 3 times (cake, fruit, pudding and pineapple).
Top with Cool Whip.

title: corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Grease and sprinkle iron frying pan with cornmeal mixture. Mix all ingredients together.
Add enough water to make a mushy mixture. Pour into pan and bake for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: kay's easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonful on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: grapefruit salad
directions: Mix and mold in grapefruit half, shells or salad molds.

title: chess tarts
directions: Combine sugar, flour and butter.
Mix.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Blend until smooth.
Pour into shells.
Bake at 450° until they start to brown (approximately 10 minutes).

title: baked squash, the american way
directions: Wash and cut squash in small pieces. Cook in small amount of water until tender, but still slightly firm. Drain. Add milk slowly to mayonnaise, stirring constantly. Add grated cheese, onion and seasonings. Put squash in casserole dish and pour sauce over it. Bake at 350° until brown on top or until firm in the center of casserole, about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: egg custard
directions: Slightly beat eggs.
Add sugar, milk and vanilla.
Pour into pie crust and bake at 350°, until brown and firm.

title: party mix
directions: In a large shallow baking pan, mix pop corn, pretzel sticks and cheese curls.
Melt butter in small saucepan.
Stir in seasonings.

title: grilled lemonade chicken
directions: Blend all ingredients together and marinate chicken in mixture for 1 hour.
Place chicken on grill.
Baste with marinade several times during the last 10 minutes of cooking.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Slice cookies and place on greased pizza pan, flattening them to make the crust.
Bake at 350° for 9 to 10 minutes.
Mix Cool Whip with softened cream cheese.
Spread on cooled crust.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Thaw broccoli in microwave and drain.
Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: lunch box cookies
directions: This is my husband, Bill's, current favorite cookie.
It is a good chewy oatmeal cookie and the recipe can be doubled.

title: homemade brown rice
directions: Mix butter, chopped onion and rice in saucepan.
Saute on high; stir continuously until golden brown.

title: sweet and sour meat balls
directions: Take leftover turkey, beef, chicken or pork and cut into small pieces.
Use leftover carrots and potatoes.
Cut into small pieces.
Add one can of peas, drained.
Salt and pepper to taste. Put gravy into mixture.
Stir well.
Make pie crust for top or Pillsbury biscuits.
Bake at 350°.

title: salami appetizer
directions: Spread slice of salami with cream cheese; continue layering until last slice (don't put cheese on this); put stack wrapped in Saran Wrap in freezer until good and cold and remove slices.
With sharp knife, cut into small wedge shaped pieces.
Serve with crackers.
Low in calories.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix together the cranberry sauce and crushed pineapple.
Mix together the whipped cream, cream cheese, mayonnaise, confectioners sugar and walnuts.
Layer the cranberry-pineapple mixture, then layer the second mixture.
Freeze.
Thaw only slightly before serving on lettuce leaves.

title: zucchini muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spray a muffin pan with Pam.
Divide equally into 12 cups.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.
Great for dieting!

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix and place in airtight container in refrigerator.
Each day for 3 days stir.
On fourth day, make into rolls and bake in 200° oven for 8 hours.
Roll over when 1/2 done.
You can use hot pepper if you prefer.

title: enchiladas
directions: Mix and heat first 5 ingredients in large boiler.
Brown ground beef in skillet.
Fry tortillas.
Dip fried tortillas in sauce mixture.
Put in layer and top with ground beef, onions and cheese. Repeat layers until finished.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix together.
Put in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: hamburg casserole
directions: Dice celery, green pepper and onion.
Brown in a skillet with hamburg.
Put in a baking dish and add soups, water and rice.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sugarless bars
directions: Cook in saucepan, dates, prunes, raisins and water. Boil slowly for 5 minutes. Remove from heat and add butter. In another bowl, combine flour, salt
and soda. Add flour mixture to fruit mixture. Add eggs and then nuts. Bake in a greased 9 X 13 pan 25 to 30 minutes at 350°. Cool. Cut into bars. Keep refrigerated or frozen.

title: goodbye turkey casserole
directions: Melt butter; add flour, onion salt, 1/2 of salt and stir in milk.
Cook over hot water, stirring until thick.
Pour rice (right from box) into 2-quart shallow baking dish.	Combine broth, 1/2 of salt and pour over rice.
Sprinkle 1/2 of cheese over, top with asparagus, then turkey or chicken.
Pour on sauce.
Sprinkle with rest of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.	Top with slivered almonds (optional).
Serves 6.

title: baked broccoli and onions
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain and place in baking dish.
Drain onions and arrange through the broccoli.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions, just until tender. Drain.
Line 14 x 10-inch pan with broccoli.
Cut Velveeta into large chunks and place over broccoli.
Drizzle half of melted butter over broccoli and Velveeta.
Mix crushed Ritz with remainder of butter.
Spread Ritz mixture over broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbles.

title: apple cake
directions: Cook apples, 1 tablespoon butter and 1 tablespoon sugar until soft.
Beat egg, 1/2 cup sugar and 1 stick butter.
Mix in baking powder, flour and lemon flavoring by hand.

title: impossible pie
directions: Put in blender.
Put in pie plate.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Add 1 cup coconut or any fruit.

title: dana's garden dip
directions: With electric mixer, beat cream cheese until smooth. Gradually add remaining ingredients; chill.
Serve with raw vegetables.

title: potato skins
directions: Bake several potatoes in oven or microwave until soft when pressed.
Let cool about 30 minutes.
Slice in half lengthwise. Scoop out center of potato, leaving about 1/2-inch or less potato on skin.
Drop skins in deep fat fryer and fry until crisp or bake in oven until crisp.
Place on broiler rack in oven, topped with shredded cheese and bacon bits.
(Fresh cooked bacon is much better.)
Broil until cheese melts.
Remove and top with more bacon bits and sour cream or your choice of toppings (green onions, chopped).
If you don't want your skins crisp, use the oven method instead of deep frying; also cuts down on calories.

title: beef stroganoff-modified
directions: Cook beef in nonstick skillet over low heat until browned. Reserving 1/2 cup bouillon, stir remaining bouillon, ketchup and garlic into skillet.
Cover and simmer until beef is tender, 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Stir in mushrooms and onion.
Stir together reserved bouillon and cornstarch until blended.
Add to beef mixture and stir.
Heat to boiling and boil 1 minute, stirring constantly. Remove from heat, stir in yogurt and light sour cream.
Serve beef over cooked noodles.

title: communion bread
directions: Combine flour, sugar, salt and butter.
Mix like pie dough into crumbs.
Add the cream and milk.
Mix well and begin to knead.
We divide the dough into 2 to 3 parts and knead.
Then divide your dough and pass one part to the next person to be kneaded with their dough.
We've found it takes 30 to 45 minutes of kneading.
When small blisters appear on the dough when you "spank" it, it is ready to be rolled out.
Roll out to approximately 3/8 to 1/2 inch thickness.
Divide and mark.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned, approximately 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and let cool.
Wrap in dampened linen type tea towels and store in refrigerator for 1 to 2 days before use.
I wrap it all individually and freeze until needed.

title: savory chicken squares
directions: Blend cream cheese and butter; add chicken.
Add and mix rest of ingredients.
Separate crescent rolls into 4 rectangles.
Press perforations to seal.
Put chicken mixture on each square.
Fold corners to center and seal.
Brush with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: cheese and bacon frittata
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease
a
9 x 9-inch pan.
In
a medium bowl, beat eggs, milk, butter, onion, salt and pepper with wire whisk. Sprinkle cheese and bacon evenly over top.
Bake 20 minutes or until set and golden brown.

title: puffy coated onion rings
directions: Remove skins and slice onions 1/4 inch thick.
Separate into rings.
Beat egg yolks.
Add buttermilk, oil and sift dry ingredients.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into buttermilk mixture.
Dip onion rings into batter.
Fry a few at a time into oil heated to 375°.

title: nan's cake
directions: Mix and bake yellow cake mix as usual.
When finished, punch holes in cake and pour pineapple juice in it.
Mix all other ingredients, adding pineapple last.
Put on cake.

title: gloria's banana nut bread
directions: *Substitute buttermilk with 1/2 cup milk mixed with 1/2 teaspoon vinegar.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix crackers with melted butter.
Mix altogether except chicken and cracker mix.
Put 1/2 crackers on the bottom of a greased casserole dish.
Pour mixture on next, then chicken. Layer chicken.
Put the rest of crackers on the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cover with foil, then uncover to brown.

title: toasted cheese rolls
directions: Trim crusts from bread.
Spread with butter.
Mix cheeses, mayonnaise and thyme.
Spread on buttered bread and carefully roll up.
Place, seam side down, in shallow baking pan.
Melt 1/4 cup butter and spoon over rolls.
Bake in 450° oven 6 minutes or until toasted.
Cut each roll into 2 pieces.
Serve hot.
Makes 16 pieces.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: sweet and sour meat loaf
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together.
In separate bowl, mix other 4 ingredients.
Add 1/2 of second mixture to meat mixture.
Pour other 1/2 on top when ready to bake.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: baked chicken in gravy
directions: Wash chicken and sprinkle with salt.
Roll in flour and brown quickly in skillet with oil.
Remove each piece of chicken as it browns and place in deep baking dish.
When all chicken pieces have been browned and placed in baking dish, pour excess oil from skillet, saving the brownings in the skillet.

title: cream cheese chicken
directions: Season chicken as if you are going to flour and fry it.
Mix can of cream of mushroom soup with packet of cheese.
Re-fill can with water and pour into the mixture.
Stir well.
Place chicken in pan that has been sprayed with Pam cooking spray and cover with cheese mixture.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes or until chicken is a golden brown color.
(Best if served hot over hot rice.
Use cheese mix as gravy.)

title: pasta supreme
directions: Cook noodles in salt water.
Saute onion, mushrooms and green pepper until tender, but not brown.
Use Pam.
Combine 2 cans of tomatoes with sauteed onion, mushrooms and green pepper.
Add spaghetti sauce, basil, salt and parsley flakes.
Add cooked, drained sausage.
Mix all these ingredients into noodles.
Put in a greased 9 x 14-inch casserole dish.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: it's better than potato salad
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Chill.
Add mayonnaise or Miracle Whip, celery, onion, mustard and salt.
Mix well.
Chill.
Stir in eggs, radishes and cucumber before serving. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: connecticut bean pot
directions: Pierce Italian sausages several time with fork.
In skillet cook Italian and onion over medium heat until onion is soft; drain.
Cut all sausages in half lengthwise.
In dutch oven or oven proof casserole, combine remaining ingredients, top with onion.
Place sausages, cut side down, over onion.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour at 350°.
Skim fat before serving.
Serves 6 to 8 servings.
