title: "no bake cookies"
directions: Mix first five ingredients and cook five minutes (time from point of boil); stir occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and oats.
Drop by spoonful onto wax paper and let set up.

title: herbed chicken
directions: Stew chicken; cool.
Reserving 2 cups broth, remove chicken from bone and tear into bite size pieces; place in shallow 3-quart baking dish.
Combine soups and 1 cup of broth; pour over the chicken.
Mix butter and remaining 1 cup broth.
Stir in stuffing. Spoon over chicken.
Bake in 400° oven for 30 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together. This can be microwaved or baked in a 350° oven.

title: raspberry tarts
directions: Mix together.
Make into a roll.
Put in refrigerator overnight. Roll out thin. Cut with wine glass. Put thumbprint in center.
Put a drop of raspberry jam in thumbprint.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Sprinkle or sift powdered sugar over after they come out of the oven.

title: pineapple turnover biscuits
directions: Combine pineapple, sugar, butter and cinnamon.
Divide into 10 muffin cups.
Center each with either a pecan or walnut half.
Add 1 teaspoon pineapple juice to each cup.
Top with refrigerated biscuits.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Invert pan immediately on serving plate.
Cool 1 minute before removing from pan.
The topping will be on the bottom.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour boiling water over oats. Let stand 20 minutes. Cream sugars and oleo.
Beat eggs, vanilla, salt and cinnamon.
Add flour, soda and oatmeal.
Mix well and bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: holiday nachos
directions: Combine soup and salsa; heat.
Pour over tortilla chips; top with the rest.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Grapes can be substituted for pecans.

title: oatmeal cinnamon muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Line muffin pan with baking cups.
In large bowl, mix flour, oats, brown sugar, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Stir with a wooden spoon to mix.
Set aside.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix together peaches and 1 cup sugar.
Set aside.
Heat oven to 350°.
Cut 3/4 stick of margarine into 2 1/2 or 3-quart baking dish and let margarine melt in oven.
Stir batter together of 1/2 cup sugar, salt, self-rising flour and milk.
Pour over melted margarine in dish.
Do not stir.
Pour peaches on top of batter.

title: antipasta salad
directions: Cook shells according to directions on the box.
Drain well. Cube pepperoni and cheese.
Cut celery, peppers and tomatoes into small pieces.
Toss shells, pepperoni, cheese, celery, peppers, tomatoes, black olives and green olives together.

title: sweet sue cookies
directions: Beat first 3 ingredients well. Add coconut and flour. Form 1 teaspoon of dough into a ball. Place on an ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.

title: chocolate coconut cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Generously grease and flour 12-cup Bundt cake pan.
Beat cake mix (dry), sour cream, water, chocolate and eggs on low speed, scraping bowl constantly, until moistened.
Beat on medium speed, scraping bowl frequently, 3 minutes.
Fold in coconut.
Pour into pan.
Bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes; remove from pan.
Cool completely.
Mix chocolate and honey; drizzle over cake. Sprinkle with coconut.

title: holiday squares
directions: Cream sugar and oleo.
Beat in 4 eggs, one at a time.
Slowly mix in flour.
Mix in lemon juice.
Grease and flour 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Spread dough evenly with a knife.

title: streusel spice coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In mixing bowl, combine flour, rolled oats and brown sugar.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Reserve 1/2 cup of mixture and set aside.

title: texas ranger beans
directions: Mix sugar, catsup, vinegar, chili powder, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper to paste.
Add to beans and onion.
Bring to a boil.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour or until sauce is thick.

title: banana split cake
directions: Line a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with graham crackers.
Mix the cream cheese with the 10x sugar. Spread the cream cheese and sugar mixture over the graham crackers, then spread the can of undrained crushed pineapple over the cream cheese-sugar mixture.
Place the sliced bananas over the pineapple.
Spread the Cool Whip over the bananas.
Drizzle the top with chocolate syrup. Decorate with nuts and cherries. Refrigerate 4 to 6 hours and serve.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Cream together the brown and white sugars with butter.
Then add eggs and beat.
Add the mashed bananas and mix in the soda and flour alternately adding with the milk.
Last, put the nuts in. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar; add well mashed bananas. Beat in eggs, salt, soda, flour, sour milk and vanilla; mix well. Add nuts and stir only enough to mix through mixture.
Pour into 2 small or 1 large loaf pan.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix sugar, butter and eggs until creamy.
Add mashed bananas; sift together flour, baking soda and cinnamon.
Add gradually to other mixture.
Mix well.
Add nuts and bake in Pam sprayed pan for 45 minutes at 375°.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cut softened butter into flour and add sour cream. Shape into 1-inch balls and drop into small muffin pans. Bake until lightly browned.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Mix all ingredients well, except corn flakes, and put in a baking dish.
Sprinkle corn flakes on top.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until bubbly.

title: meatball stroganoff
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Roll meat into 1-inch balls. Bake at 325° for 15 minutes in an uncovered dish.

title: chocolate dessert
directions: Soften margarine and combine with flour and nuts.
Spread evenly on 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: chocolate street cookies
directions: Cover cookie sheet with foil.
Melt chocolate over hot water. Add butter.
Stir until smooth.
In mixer, beat eggs until very light in color.
Gradually add sugar, beating mixture until it is almost white and forms a ribbon when beaters are raised.
Beat in vanilla.
Add cooled chocolate; beat on low speed.
Add dry ingredients.
Beat on low only enough to blend.
Bake 12 minutes at 350°.
Cookie should be cracked on top, but soft to touch.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter and powdered sugar together until fine crumbs.
Save 1/4 cup for top of pie.
Spread the remaining mixture in bottom of pie shell.
Mix pudding by directions on box. Spread on top of sugar mixture.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle the 1/4 cup crumbs on top.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: biscuits
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in butter with pastry blender or fork.
Add eggs and enough milk to make a dough that holds together and can be kneaded.
Turn dough on a lightly floured board and knead very lightly (no more than 10 times).
Pat the dough to a thickness of approximately 1/2-inch.
Cut into rounds and bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: sweet rolls
directions: Cool milk to lukewarm.
Add sugar, salt, shortening and eggs, mixing well.
Add 5 cups of flour and yeast; mix well with mixer until smooth.
Add remaining flour to make soft dough.
Knead for 2 or 3 minutes or until smooth.
Store in refrigerator in covered bowl or large bag; will keep 5 days.
Take whatever you want at a time out of bowl.
Allow 3 hours to rise, if chilled.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Yields 6 dozen rolls.

title: chewy caramel brownies
directions: Melt the caramels with 1/3 cup evaporated milk in double boiler (medium heat, stir often) or microwave.
Combine cake mix, melted butter, and the rest of the evaporated milk. Spread half of the batter in a greased 13-inch pan.
Bake 6 minutes at 350°. Cool slightly. Spread melted caramel mixture on top and sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Spread remaining cake batter over the mixture.
(This is tricky, but it will turn out fine.)
Bake 18 minutes at 350°.
Cool and cut.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix jello into hot water and let dissolve.
Pour jello into medium pan and add cranberry sauce, pineapple, orange juice, and chopped pecans.
Mix cream cheese, sour cream, and sugar together and spread over top of salad.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Crumble 1/2 of wafers in a 12-inch dish.
Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Spread over wafers.
Put strawberries over mixture; top with Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: chess pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light. Add beaten egg yolks, flour and nuts. Add dry ingredients, vanilla and milk. Put in pastry-lined pie pan. Preheat oven to 325°. Cook about 45 minutes or until knife inserted in middle comes out clean.

title: chicken and wild rice casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Combine with chicken and soup.
Place in 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fat-free zucchini cake
directions: In a large bowl, mix all the dry ingredients.
Then in no particular order, mix in the rest of the ingredients.
Grease and flour a tube cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 60 to 75 minutes.

title: spanish steak with onions
directions: Mix garlic, vinegar, oil, oregano, black pepper, salt and Sason in bowl until mixed well.
Add already-sliced steaks; mix well.
Cover and refrigerate overnight, if possible, or at least 2 to 4 hours.

title: bread pudding
directions: In a large bowl, break up bread in bite size pieces.
Cover with milk; soak 1 hour.
Mix well and add the eggs and sugar. Stir in vanilla, cinnamon and raisins; mix and place in a large baking dish.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate and butter over low heat.
Remove from heat. Gradually blend in milk.
Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add to beaten eggs and vanilla.
Gradually blend in chocolate mixture. Pour in pie shell.
Mix coconut and pecans in a big bowl. Sprinkle over pie.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Filling will be soft, but will set while cooling.
Cool at least 4 hours before cutting.

title: drum-stick of chicken wing
directions: Brown chicken wings in a little oil.
Mix sauce and pour over chicken wings. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serve in chafing dish.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake the cake according to directions!
Put 1 cake layer on bottom of punch bowl.
Prepare instant pudding according to package directions; place on top of cake layer.
Layer the following:
1/2 can fruit cocktail, 1/2 can pineapple, 1
package strawberries, nuts, Cool Whip and coconut.
Repeat this process with the remaining ingredients in the same order.
Top off with cherries.

title: croutons
directions: Cube bread and put on a cookie sheet.
Combine butter, oil, garlic salt, parsley, basil and oregano.
Pour mixture over cubes and stir.
Bake in oven at 250° for 45 to 55 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: party potatoes
directions: Stir together all ingredients and put into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Last 15 or 20 minutes, top with grated sharp Cheddar cheese.

title: pizza lasagna
directions: Take a square dish and put cooked hamburger and mushrooms together in bottom.
Put the cheese on top, then add pizza sauce and then add Mozzarella cheese on top.
Put in oven and bake and now you have pizza lasagna.

title: layered cheese cake
directions: Mix cheese cake mix according to directions except add 1/2 cup of milk extra for each box.
On bottom of a large, deep, glass bowl, layer thin sliced pound cake, then layers of cheese cake mix, Cool Whip.
Make another layer of each.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: vegetable meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients except tomato soup in large bowl.
Mix well and loaf (makes 1 large or 2 small loaves).
Place in deep baking dish.
Pour tomato soup over loaf and bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven; spread thin layer of ketchup over loaf and bake 15 more minutes.
Slice and serve.

title: golden amaretto cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In mixing bowl, place cake mix, oil, pudding, eggs, 3/4 cup liqueur, water and almond extract. Blend well. Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground round and drain.
Place in casserole dish; add soup and mix well.
Add Tater Tots on top of mixture.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Pound flour into beef until steak is 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into strips 1/2-inch wide and 2 inches long.
Brown in butter.
Add remaining ingredients, except sour cream.
Cook over low heat, covered tightly, for 25 minutes.
Stir occasionally, then stir in sour cream.
Serve over hot, cooked noodles.
Serves 10.

title: 4 layer pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix flour, butter and pecans. Press in dish. Bake 15 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool.

title: cabbage chop suey
directions: Melt fat in skillet; add vegetables.
Cover and cook over low heat 5 minutes.
Uncover; season and continue cooking 1 minute, stirring gently.
Serve at once.
Garnish with strips of crisp bacon.
Serves 6.

title: texas favorite party dip
directions: Saute meat and onions.
Add rest of ingredients and heat on low until cheese is melted.
Serve warm with chips.

title: turkey and corn bread dressing
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter in a large saucepan until tender.
Add the corn bread and sprinkle with seasonings.
Add the egg and mix.
Add enough water to moisten and mix well.
Stuff turkey or cook separately at 400° until brown.

title: low-fat rhubarb cake
directions: Spread rhubarb in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle sugar, Jell-O and marshmallows on top of rhubarb.
Mix a yellow cake mix as directed on box.
Pour batter on top of rhubarb mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
(I set my pan on a cookie sheet to catch any drips.)

title: chocolate-peanut butter chip brownies
directions: Prepare brownie mix according to package directions.
Stir in peanut butter morsels.
Spoon mixture into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: apple crunch
directions: Mix apples with sugar, flour, cinnamon and salt. Spread in 9 x 13 pan. Mix oatmeal, brown sugar, flour and margarine until crumbly. Sprinkle evenly over apples. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°. Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: crock-pot chicken south texas
directions: Lightly grease sides and bottom of slow-cooking pot.
Arrange alternate layers of tortillas with chicken and mixture of undiluted soups, salsa, sour cream and onion.
Cover and cook on low for 4 to 5 hours.
Sprinkle with cheese and cook on low another 15 or 20 minutes.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease bottoms of 12 medium muffin cups (2 3/4 inches in diameter).
Mix all ingredients just until flour is moistened.
Batter should be lumpy.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full. Sprinkle 1/4 teaspoon sugar over batter in each cup.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes.
Immediately remove from pan.
Yields 12 muffins.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut steak into serving size pieces.
Brown steak in skillet; pour off fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook over low heat for 2 hours and 15 minutes or until tender, stirring often.

title: santa's snowflakes(cookies)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat egg whites well; add vanilla and continue beating until very firm.
Add sugar gradually beating until stiff.
Fold in nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased aluminum foil on cookie sheet.
Put in oven.
Turn off oven at once.
Leave in oven 1 hour until oven cools.

title: scones
directions: Pre-heat skillet to 380° (hi-heat).
Sift together all dry ingredients.

Make a well in the center of the sifted ingredients. Add buttermilk and egg and mix with a knife, using a light hand. Pour approximately 1/2 c. batter onto lightly floured surface and lightly flour the batter.
Using a light hand, pat down the batter with the back of your hand until it is about 1/2-inch thick.

With a clean knife, swiftly cut the batter into 4 equal sections. Gently scoop one of the sections into the palm of your hand and quickly and lightly toss back and forth a few times and drop onto a pre-heated skillet.
Repeat with other sections.
Flip when brown 3 to 5 minutes.
Cool, wrapped in a clean tea-towel.
Serve with sweet savory topping.
Always break apart, never cut!

title: creamy potato puff
directions: Mix
potatoes, cream cheese, egg and salt until creamy. Add onions
and pimento.
Put in ungreased casserole dish and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican salad
directions: Chop lettuce and put in a large bowl.
Brown ground beef and drain.
Heat Ro-Tel and cheese soup in a saucepan.
Top lettuce with Doritos, meat and sauce mixture.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar. Beat in eggs. Blend in buttermilk.
Stir in remaining ingredients just until blended.
Pour into a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan, greased on bottom only.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes.

title: brisket
directions: Bring water to boil, dissolve soup in water.
Pour over meat. Bake at 275° to 300° for 5 to 6 hours.

title: aku steaks moroccan style
directions: Combine all spices in a small bowl and blend well.
Rub each side of tuna with spice mixture and sprinkle evenly with lemon and oil.
Cover with plastic wrap and let stand for 1 hour.
Broil on a rack for 4 minutes, 4-inches from flame.
Turn and continue to cook for 3 to 4 minutes for medium done.
The steaks should be well browned.
Place on plates.
Brush with melted butter.
Sprinkle with coriander.
Serves 4 people.

title: pecan tassies
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese until well blended.
Add flour and blend well.
Chill dough for 1 hr.
Shape into 2 dozen balls. Put in muffin pan and press up sides.
Beat together egg, brown sugar, butter, vanilla and salt.
Set aside.
Divide 1 cup of pecans into each muffin cup.
Add egg mixture to each cup and top with additional pecans in each.
Bake at 325 degrees for 25 minutes.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs 5 minutes. Gradually add sugar. Add the
remaining ingredients,
mixing after each.
Pour into jelly roll pan (I line with parchment paper)
and spread evenly. Top with 1 cup chopped walnuts. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Sprinkle 10x sugar on towel. Flip cake over on towel. Let sit 2 minutes, then roll until cool. Unroll and fill.

title: italian tuna and spiral pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package; drain.
Rinse in cold water; drain.
Mix macaroni and remaining ingredients.
Serve on salad greens if desired.

title: peggy's stuffed worcester beef logs
directions: Lightly combine first 5 ingredients plus 4 teaspoons Worcestershire sauce.
Divide into 6 parts.
Shape one part beef mixture around cheese strip to form a roll.
Wrap bacon slice around each roll.
Place on jelly roll pan.
Brush liberally with Worcestershire sauce.
Bake in preheated oven at 475` for 15 to 18 minutes or until done as desired, brushing once more with sauce. Serves 6.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: family favorite
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese dinner as directed.
Brown ground round with onion and bell pepper; cook until vegetables are tender.
Combine macaroni and cheese with ground round; add the soup.
Mix well.
Place in casserole dish and bake at 350° until hot and bubbly.
Serves 4.

title: artichoke and mushroom casserole
directions: Place butter pats at bottom of casserole.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Add a layer of artichokes and a layer of mushrooms.
Pat over with butter.
Repeat until full.
Bake at 350° for 3 minutes.

title: easy meatballs
directions: Mix meat with all ingredients, adding the boiling water last. Blend well.
Shape into 24 meatballs.
Place on cookie sheet and bake in 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes, until lightly brown.
Add to your homemade sauce or use bottled sauce.
Good with spaghetti or as a meatball sandwich.

title: southern fruit pie
directions: Mix all together and pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell. Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: jello chiffon pie
directions: Whip the cream and add sugar and lemon juice.
Whip in the box of Jell-O until mixed well.
Put into the pie shells.
Chill for 1 hour.

title: peppered corn casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add tomatoes, drained whole kernel corn, drained Shoe Peg corn and creamed corn.
Refrigerate at least 8 hours.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.
Serves 8.

title: ham-swiss cheese sandwich
directions: Place ham and cheese slices on 4 slices bread.
Top with remaining bread slices.
Spread outsides of sandwiches with butter. Grill in skillet over low to medium heat for 5 to 7 minutes on each side or brown in a sandwich grill for 5 to 7 minutes.
Makes 4 sandwiches.

title: microwave potatoes and cheese
directions: In microwavable bowl, mix potatoes and butter.
Cover and microwave until potatoes are soft (approximately 15 minutes).
Add cheese and bacon bits.
Stir and microwave another 1 to 2 minutes until cheese melts.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Mix crumbs, butter, peanut butter and sugar in bowl.
Mix until smooth.
Put into buttered 9 x 9-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips in pan over low heat. Spread over mixture.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: taco pie
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain grease.
Add seasoning and water.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add refried beans.
Sprinkle 1/2 of Doritos in pie crust bottom.
Spread meat over Doritos and press down.
Next spread sour cream over meat, then sprinkle rest of Doritos.
Put cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: pear honey
directions: Heat until transparent and seal.

title: chicken curry
directions: Marinate chicken in yogurt overnight or 2 to 3 hours before cooking.
Place 3 tablespoons of oil in a 3 to 5-quart pan.
Add onion, chicken (yogurt also), ginger, garlic, cumin, cinnamon, cloves, cardamom, turmeric, chili powder and 1/2 cup hot water. Mix. Bring to a boil; reduce heat and cook for 1/2 hour.
Stir occasionally.
After water evaporates and oil begins to rise (around sides), stir gently and cook an additional 5 minutes.
Add potatoes and green chilies.
Cook 20 more minutes or until potato is tender.
If desired, add a little more cinnamon.

title: oyster fritters
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Pour oysters and liquid in medium size bowl.
Cut with kitchen scissors.
Add dry ingredients, a little at a time, to prevent flour from clumping. Mix well with fork.
Try not to crush oyster pieces.
Use large frying pan, medium-hot Crisco oil 1/2 inch deep.
Dip using ladle; fry until golden brown.
Flip.
Drain on paper towels.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Peel, cook, drain and mash sweet potatoes.
(Can use those found in can, heat in microwave.)
While still hot, add butter, milk, eggs and vanilla.
Mix well and pat into casserole dish. Mix together the pecans, brown sugar, stick of margarine and flour.
Sprinkle on top of potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: spinach terrific(vegetable side dish)
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: italian nut cookies
directions: Butter brown paper to fit cookie sheet.
Combine flour and sugar with bread crumbs.
Add egg yolks and extracts until frothy. Add to flour.
Beat until combined.
If you pinch dough and it holds together, it's right.
Add nuts.
Work into dough with hands until it holds together.
Divide in half.
Shape into 2 x 12-inch logs.
Beat egg white.
Brush over logs.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°. Cool for 1 hour.
Cut into 1-inch cookies.
Bake 10 minutes. Makes 4 dozen.

title: lemon cheesecake
directions: Stir cream cheese until very soft.
Blend in 1/2 cup milk. Add remaining milk and the pudding mix; beat slowly with eggbeater until well mixed, about 1 minute (do not overbeat).
Pour at once into graham cracker crust.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs lightly over top.
Chill about an hour.
Serves 8.

title: reduced fat tuna cheese potato
directions: Bake potato until done.
Cool.
Cut in half lengthwise.
Scoop out potato being careful not to tear skin.
Saute celery, onion and green pepper in margarine.
Mash potato with fork and stir in remaining ingredients except cheese.
Divide mixture into each shell.
Bake on cookie sheet 10 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 5 minutes more until cheese melts. Makes 2 servings 283 calories; 9 grams fat; 24 mg. cholesterol per serving.

title: fruit punch
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Serves 25 people (3 gallons).

title: poinsettia cocktail
directions: Combine the vodka, champagne and juice in a large-stemmed red wine glass.
Add crushed ice and stir until the mixture is well chilled.
Twist the orange strips over the glass; drop them in and serve. Makes 1 cocktail.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Cream together, butter, brown sugar, eggs, vanilla and sour cream.
Mix flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Then add to creamed mixture.
Chill.

title: caramel-pecan pinwheels
directions: In a 9 x 1 1/2-inch round baking pan, stir together caramel ice cream topping and melted butter or margarine.
Arrange pecan halves over caramel mixture.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Season to taste with salt and pepper.
I also use chicken flavored bouillon crystals.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Chop apples; add remaining ingredients.
Stir well and chill 1 hour before serving.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix well and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° until pumpkin is thickened and crust is done.

title: raw vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well and refrigerate for 1 hour before serving.
Serve with assorted raw vegetables for dipping.

title: rio grande meat loaf
directions: Combine all of the above ingredients.
Shape into 8 or 10 individual loaves or put in muffin pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: wassail(a good holiday drink)
directions: Combine juices and sugar in crock-pot.
Stick cloves all around in the orange and cut in slices.
Place orange slices and cinnamon sticks in mixture.
Simmer on low heat for 1 hour.

title: pickled mushrooms
directions: Combine all ingredients, except mushrooms; bring to a boil. Add mushrooms and simmer 5 minutes.
Chill overnight.
Drain and serve with toothpicks.
Can make several days ahead and keep in refrigerator (even 2 weeks).

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding with milk.
Add Cool Whip and sour cream.
Layer with bananas and wafers.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: miniature cherry cheesecake
directions: You will need foil cupcake liners.

title: easy but delicious fruit tart
directions: Flour bottom of tart pan and add crust.
Bake unfilled pie crust at 450° for 15 minutes.
Let cool.
Blend together next 4 ingredients and pour into cooled baked shell.
Let chill 45 minutes.
Arrange fresh fruit slices on top of cream cheese mixture.
Melt jelly and pour over fruit for glaze.
Let chill and serve.

title: mom's strawberry glaze pie
directions: Crush 1 cup of the smaller berries and cook with water about 2 minutes, then mash the berries.
Combine the sugar and cornstarch; stir into the berry juice.
Cook and stir until clear.
Add the food coloring.
Place 1/2 the remaining berries in the baked pastry shell.
Pour half of the sauce over the berries.
Repeat with the remaining berries and sauce.
Chill for several hours until set.
Serve with Cool Whip!

title: nutty fingers
directions: Blend sugar and margarine until creamy. Add flour, vanilla and pecans. Shape dough into fingers. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: pineapple souffle
directions: Mix eggs and sugar.
Add margarine.
Cream until smooth.
Add pineapple.
Cube bread and fold in.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: candy bars
directions: Prepare a buttered cookie sheet with sides (jelly roll pan). Place peanut butter into greased large bowl. Cook the sugar, Karo and water to 290°.
Pour into peanut butter. Stir quickly and pour into prepared pan.
Press flat. Score and cut into pieces.
Melt chocolate over warm water. Drop candy into chocolate and onto wax paper to set.
Wrap in foil or plastic wrap.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add eggs, cooking oil, apple pie filling and vanilla.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Scald milk.
Add sugar and salt.
Dissolve yeast in well. Add melted shortening and remaining flour, using only enough flour to make dough handle well.
Knead until smooth.
Place in a greased bowl; set in warm place to rise until double in bulk. Make into rolls.
This can also be refrigerated and made into rolls the next day.

title: texas trash
directions: Melt margarine, drippings and seasoning.
Simmer for 10 minutes (do not boil).
Pour over dry ingredients and roast for 1 to 1/2 hours at 250°, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Boil chicken breasts with bay leaf. Combine onion and green chiles with butter. Saute until onion is cooked (I microwave 10 minutes, stirring every 2 minutes). Mix cream cheese with onion mixture. Combine well. Mix finely chopped chicken. Put about 3 tablespoons of this mixture in a flour tortilla. Roll and place seam side down in pan (9 x 13). Cover with Monterey Jack cheese. Pour whipping cream over all. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. This should make 12 tortillas.

title: r o's barbecue slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pack in clean pint jars; seal.
Place in refrigerator.
Flavor improves as it sits.

title: mex-chili bake
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan (or large skillet), heat oil.
Add onions and garlic.
Saute until soft.
Add turkey, peppers and taco seasoning.
Cook until done (3 minutes), stirring to break up meat.
Sprinkle chili powder, salt and pepper.
Continue to cook and stir.
Stir in tomatoes.
Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in macaroni and transfer to 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake covered 45 minutes.
Remove cover; sprinkle with cheese and heat 5 minutes before serving.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Mix and pour over chicken and bake. I use boneless and skinless chicken breasts. Bake at 350°, covered, a little more than an hour, until chicken is tender.

title: lemon yogurt tea bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 4 (4 x 2 1/2-inch) loaf pans with cooking spray.
From lemons, grate peel and squeeze 2 tablespoons juice.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt. With pastry blender or two knives used scissor-fashion, cut in corn oil spread until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in yogurt, egg substitute, lemon extract, lemon peel and lemon juice just until flour is moistened.
Spoon batter into loaf pans.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes, until toothpick inserted in center of bread comes out clean. Immediately remove from pan.
Serve warm, or cool on wire rack to serve later.

title: spaghetti sauce with meat
directions: Brown meat; drain grease.
Sprinkle flour to absorb grease. Add onion and garlic; cook until tender.
Add tomato sauce and 1 can water and tomato paste and 2 cans of water.
Stir thoroughly; cook on high until it comes to a boil.
Reduce heat to low; cook 1 1/2 hours.
Cover with lid; stir occasionally.
Remove bay leaves and serve on 16 to 24 ounces of cooked spaghetti.

title: persimmon cookies
directions: In a large bowl, mix together all ingredients until well mixed.
With a tablespoon, spoon out spoonfuls of cookie dough. Place them on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake in the oven at 350° for approximately 15 minutes.
Be careful.
Do not over bake.

title: cinnamon crisps
directions: Sift the first 3 ingredients together; set aside.
Cream the butter until softened.
Add the sugar gradually, creaming until fluffy.
Alternately add dry ingredients in fourths and milk in thirds to creamed mixture, mixing until blended after each addition.
Using small amount of dough at a time, roll out dough about 1/8-inch thick on a well floured surface.
Cut into 2-inch squares. Transfer to a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Melt 1 stick oleo in a 9 x 13-inch pan in oven. Add rice, onion and celery.
Brown. Stir often. Add mushroom soup and water; mix well. Place chicken on top of rice mixture and bake at 350° until chicken is tender and browned.
Stir once or twice to keep rice from sticking.
May have to add water if it gets too dry before chicken is tender.

title: egg and sausage souffle
directions: Brown sausage and drain. Beat eggs.
Add milk, salt and mustard.
Add cubed bread and stir.
Add cheese and sausage.
Pour into glass baking dish (9 x 13-inch).
Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let sit a few minutes before serving.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Place in greased casserole; bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour or until knife comes out of center clean.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pilgrim's ale
directions: Combine juices in large bowl (punch bowl best).
Chill and serve.

title: tuna-noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions; drain and set aside in a saucepan.
Cook celery and onions in butter or margarine until tender, but not brown.
Add flour.
Stir in condensed soup.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook and stir until mixture is thick and bubbly.
Add tuna, pimento and cooked noodles and carefully stir.
Turn noodle mixture into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle the Parmesan cheese over top of mixture. Bake, uncovered, in 375° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Garnish with sprigs of parsley, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: You will need one greased or Pam sprayed jelly roll pan with sides.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti in chicken broth.
Cook onion and pepper in small amount
of
broth.
Mash tomatoes with potato masher. Drain spaghetti; add
other
ingredients.
Stir
over low heat until cheese melts.
Pour
into
baking
dish and bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: bacon and cheese hoagie
directions: Butter both sides of Hoagie bun and broil in oven for 2-3 minutes.
Take out of oven and place shredded Mozzarella cheese on one side of Hoagie.
Then place lettuce, tomato slices and bacon strips on top of cheese.
Fold Hoagie together and place back in oven for 5- 7 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Take out and drip olive oil inside of Hoagie.
Spread Mayonnaise on top inside bun (optional).

title: spinach with sour cream casserole
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions. Drain well. Add onion soup and sour cream. Blend well. Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole and top with the herb stuffing mix and melted butter. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: tacos bel grande
directions: Cook ground beef (chopped) until well done.
Stir in onion and drained mushrooms; mix well.
From taco kit, stir in taco sauce and taco seasoning; mix well.
It will be dry.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam or other nonstick spray.
Fill soft taco shells with mixture.
Lay them in the pan with one slightly on top of the other.
Top with cheese.
Any kind of cheese works well. Top with picante sauce or salsa.
Bake in the oven at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes, until cheese has melted.

title: turtles brownies
directions: Melt caramels with 1/3 cup evaporated milk over low heat, stirring until smooth.
Combine remaining milk with dry cake mix and margarine.
Press 1/2 of cake mix into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Spread chocolate pieces and pecans over hot cake.
Then spread melted caramel mixture over top.
Spread to edge of pan.
Crumble rest of dough over caramel.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Do not overbake. Cool and cut.

title: colonial peanut soup
directions: Melt butter in a saucepan over low heat; add onion and celery. Saute for about 5 minutes.
Add flour and mix until well blended. Stir in chicken broth and allow to simmer for about 30 minutes. Remove from heat; strain broth.
Stir the peanut butter, salt and lemon juice into the strained broth until well mixed.
Serve hot in cups.
Garnish each cup with a teaspoon of chopped peanuts. Yields:
6 servings.

title: custard
directions: Combine egg yolks, sugar and salt; stir in scalded milk. Cook over hot water, stirring constantly, until mixture coats a spoon. Remove from heat; add vanilla. Chill and it is ready to drink.

title: pimento cheese spread
directions: Combine all cheese, pimentos, relish and a little salt to taste.
Blend with enough mayonnaise to get the consistency you desire.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Wash cabbage and shred.
Put in heavy skillet in which bacon drippings have been melted and are hot.
Cover and let fry slowly over a medium heat. Stir occasionally.
Season with salt and pepper. Serve with buttered cornbread.

title: swiss custard
directions: Fry and drain bacon; crumble and divide into four large custard dishes.
Beat 4 eggs well.
Add Swiss cheese, grated Parmesan, milk and salt.
Pour over bacon pieces in dishes. Sprinkle 1/8 teaspoon nutmeg on each serving.
Place custard dishes in 2 (8 x 11-inch) pans and surround with 1-inch hot water. Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or until set.

title: taco casserole
directions: Crumble beef into a 2-quart casserole.
Microwave on High for 5 to 6 minutes.
Drain.
Stir in seasonings and water.
Microwave 2 more minutes.
Stir in chips and 1 1/2 cups cheese and microwave 2 1/2 more minutes or until heated through.
Stir and top with chopped tomatoes and remaining cheese.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Mix all together and roll into balls.
Roll in sugar.
Bake about 9 minutes at 375.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and shape into balls.
Bake on cookie sheet at 375° until brown (15 minutes).

title: crock-pot dressing
directions: Saute onions and celery.
Mix all ingredients.
Place in crock-pot.
Cook 1 hour on high and 4 hours on low.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and top with crushed cornflakes mixed with butter.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Put butter in a casserole dish.
Let melt.
Combine flour, milk and sugar together.
Stir.
Pour peaches in butter, then pour liquid crust on top of peaches.
Let cook for 30 minutes at 375°.

title: stuffed cabbage casserole
directions: Cook rice as directed, omitting butter if called for.
While rice is cooking, fill a large pot with water, about 3/4 full, and boil.
Core and cut the cabbage into 2-inch pieces and place in water to blanch.
Drain cabbage.
Saute turkey in large pan along with onion.
Add salt, pepper, stewed tomatoes and tomato saue and stir well, breaking up tomatoes.
Add cooked rice, blanched cabbage, lemon juice and brown sugar, mix well.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: chocolate chip cookies(diabetic)
directions: Cream margarine until light.
Add sweetener, water, vanilla and egg.
Mix well.
Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Add to creamed mixture.
Combine chocolate morsels and nuts; add to dough and blend well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased bakery sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: diabetic applesauce raisin cake
directions: Cook raisins in water until water evaporates.
Mix all other ingredients together with raisins.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes or until center is done.

title: breakfast muffins(yields 12 muffins)
directions: Stir all ingredients together with a spoon.
Spray muffin tin with Pam.
Fill muffin cups 3/4 full.
Bake t 375° approximately for 15 minutes.
Delicious and nutritional.

title: strawberry-banana brownies(in honor of blue bull 75)
directions: Remove stems and hulls from strawberries.
Mash together strawberries and banana; set aside.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Build in the order given in a punch bowl twice.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Serves 35 people.

title: stuffed mushroom caps
directions: Clean mushrooms and remove stems (save stems).
Put in shallow greased (with olive oil) baking dish.
Finely chop the stems. Heat 2 tablespoons olive oil in skillet.
Add mushroom stems, onion and garlic.
Cook until slightly browned.
In another bowl, mix bread crumbs, cheese, parsley, salt and oregano.
Mix in onion mixture.
Fill caps.
Pour 2 tablespoons olive oil into baking dish.
Bake uncovered at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes, until slightly browned.

title: chicken rolls
directions: Toss chicken in bowl with salad oil, oregano and salt; set aside.
In bowl with cucumber, add yogurt, garlic and salt.

title: cheese soup
directions: Combine beef broth, onion and celery powder and heat to boiling.
Stir in cheese, blending well; reduce heat and heat until cheese is melted.
Stir well before serving.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and margarine together.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into 3 small pie crusts (two 9-inch).
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Decrease heat to 300° and bake approximately 35 more minutes.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add salt and 2 cups flour.
Add rest of flour on bread board.
Knead until stiff; roll out thin and let dry.
Cut in thin strips.
Can be frozen.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Mix and let set, using a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: sunday morning waffles
directions: Pour the milk into a large mixing bowl; sprinkle the yeast over the top.
Stir well to dissolve, making certain that no lumps remain.
Beat egg yolks; add to cooled yeast mixture.
Combine the flour, salt, sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg; add to mixture.
Add the vanilla.
Stir in the melted butter.
Combine completely.
Beat the egg whites until stiff; fold into the batter.
Let the mixture stand in a warm place for 1 hour, or until doubled in size.
Using a regular waffle iron, fill the tray with 1 1/2 cups of mixture. Cook until golden brown.

title: paul's barbecue sauce
directions: Mix ingredients together and season to taste.
Great for barbecue chicken.

title: chicken salad
directions: Boil hen, onion and celery stalks until chicken is tender. Discard onion and celery. Cut chicken into small pieces.
Marinate in lemon juice overnight.
Add celery.
Add almonds to chicken. Mix well.

title: sweet and sour chicken breast
directions: Remove skin and bone from chicken breast (or use boneless). Salt and pepper.
Have frying pan medium hot.
I use Pam.
You may use a small bit of oil.
Brown on both sides and drain.
Cut in strips.
Mix together peach preserves and barbecue sauce diluted with water.
Layer chicken in a casserole dish.
Put a generous amount of the peach and barbecue sauce over chicken.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° covered with foil.
This can be served over rice.

title: betsy's peach topping for cake or ice cream
directions: Combine all ingredients and heat in the microwave until thoroughly heated and sugar is dissolved.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Crush berries; add sugar and water and cook 2 minutes and strain.
Add cornstarch and cook until clear.
Add butter and food coloring.
Pour over after the glaze has cooled down, then serve with Cool Whip, if desired.

title: beef stew
directions: Drain all vegetables except tomatoes.
Combine all ingredients in Dutch oven pot with cover.
Bake at 250° for 6 to 7 hours, covered.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Beat butter at medium speed with electric mixer about 2 minutes or until soft and creamy. Gradually add sugar, beating on medium speed 5 to 7 minutes. Add eggs one at a time, beating just until yellow disappears. Combine flour and baking soda; add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream, beginning and ending with flour mixture. Mix at lowest speed just until blended after each addition. Stir in flavorings. Pour into 9 x 12 cake pan or Bundt cake pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until spongy.

title: hamburger onion pie
directions: Brown onion, beef, garlic, salt and pepper in skillet.
Drain off excess fat.
Pour into a baking dish and add tomato paste and vegetable soup.
Mix together.
Arrange biscuits over top of this and bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: asparagus canapes
directions: Trim crusts.
Flatten bread.
Blend cheese and egg.
Spread on bread.
Roll 1 spear of asparagus in each slice.
Dip in melted butter.
Freeze.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Brown meat and
drain.
In a slow cooker, place cheese, tomatoes, Worcestershire
sauce
and
chili
powder,
then the meat.
Cook on
high
until cheese melts, stirring frequently. Cook on high for 1
hour.
(May
be cooked on low to keep warm for serving, up to 6 hours.)

title: dilled salmon
directions: Microwave butter until melted.
Stir in lemon and cream. Place fish in mixture and turn to coat both sides.
Sprinkle each with dill.
Cover with plastic.
Let sit in refrigerator for 20 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 40 minutes.

title: twinkles quick rolls
directions: Mix water and yeast.
Heat milk, sugar, salt and butter to lukewarm.
Combine flour with above.
Let rise approximately 1 hour.
Punch down.
Make rolls; let rise 30 minutes.
Bake at 375° until light brown.

title: soy flour tofu
directions: Sift the flour and add it to the boiling water.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
(Stir frequently; do not let it boil over.)
Remove from heat and slowly add lemon juice (one tablespoon at a time).
The less you stir the bigger the curds will be.
Let it sit for 5 to 10 minutes.
Pour into a colander lined with cheesecloth or similar cloth to drain.
May run water through it, if desired.
Use as is for scrambled tofu or season as desired for salads, etc.
To form, squeeze out the remaining liquid and press into plastic container. Cover and refrigerate.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Place chicken in bottom of dish, salt and pepper to taste. Mix soups and 1 soup can of milk together. Pour over chicken. Take 1 1/2 cups chicken broth and add one stick butter, stir until melted. Mix herb dressing mix with broth and place over chicken and soup. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Dissolve chocolate in 1/2 cup boiling water.
Cream Crisco and sugar; add beaten egg yolks.
Add 3/4 cup buttermilk alternately with flour. Dissolve soda in remaining buttermilk.
Add salt to chocolate.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in three 9-inch pans at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook sausage, layer in casserole dish with thawed Tater Tots. Mix up.
Beat eggs with a little milk. Pour over Tater Tots.
Add onion and cheese.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: aloha punch
directions: Boil the sugar in the water for 3 minutes. Cool and add the fruit juice and pineapple.
Pour over cracked ice before serving.

title: crust for cream pies
directions: Cut margarine into flour and sugar until crumbly.
Press into bottom and sides of 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 325° until brown; cool.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: Beat egg yolks and 1/2 cup sugar until thick and smooth.
Add pumpkin, milk and spices.
Cook in double boiler until thick.
Add gelatin, softened in cold water; stir until dissolved.
Cool.
Add egg whites, beaten stiff, with sugar.
Pour into baked pie shells. Fill 2 shells.

title: chicken nuggets
directions: Mix butter crackers, Parmesan cheese, salt, thyme, basil and pepper.
Cover baking sheet with foil.
Heat oven to 400°.
Dip chicken pieces into melted butter, then crumb mixture.
Place chicken on baking sheet and bake until golden brown, 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pound cake cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and other ingredients.
Drop by 1/2 teaspoon on greased sheet.
Bake about 10 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken pie
directions: Combine chicken broth, milk and oleo and bring to boil to melt oleo; thicken with the flour.
Put layer of chicken in casserole dish, then layer of sliced boiled eggs and half the broth mixture. Top with crust that has been rolled out thin and bake at 400° until done and real brown.
Repeat layer for the second time and again bake at 400°.
I cut crust with glass, it makes it easier to spoon when serving.
I also use a dish 10 x 12-inches, about 3-inches deep

title: french cheese ball
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Form into a ball. Roll in parsley and walnuts. Chill. Serve with crackers.

title: punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add sugar; stir until dissolved and let cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Add the amount of water called for on the frozen juices.
Chill and serve.

title: rainbow reuben salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; drain.
Rinse with cold water to cool quickly; drain well.
In large bowl, combine remaining ingredients and cooled pasta; toss until evenly blended. Chill and serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: swedish stew
directions: Slice potato and put layer in baking bowl.
Add layer of onions and little tomatoes smashed.
Sprinkle with garlic salt.
Repeat layers ending with hamburger patties.
Pour rest of tomatoes over all, then garlic salt and sugar.
Cover tightly with foil and bake 2 1/2 to 3 hours in 325° oven.

title: sour cream dill bread
directions: Soften margarine and yeast in large mixing bowl.
Stir in 1/2 teaspoon salt, 1 tablespoon margarine and next 6 ingredients.
Then add half the flour and beat well.
Add enough more flour to make a stiff dough.
Turn out on lightly floured board and knead 5 to 10 turns.
Put back in bowl and let rise in warm place until doubled in bulk, about 1 hour.
Shape into two loaves.
Put each in greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Let rise 30 to 40 minutes.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes.
Brush with margarine and sprinkle with salt.

title: turkey ham with cherry glaze
directions: This recipe came from an Antle Family cookbook put together by our mother's cousin and her daughter.
Ollie is in her nineties now so this recipe is very old.
Ollie wrote, "I found this recipe on a folded slip of yellowed paper tucked into an old cookbook that hadn't been opened for 30 years.
It was written in my father's hand.
Beside it was the reduced recipe written in my late husband's Palmer Method writing."
Ollie's father was James F. Antle, my grandfather, Alvin Antle's oldest brother.

title: chili cheese bread
directions: Slice bread horizontally and set aside.
Grate cheese and mix with mayonnaise; add drained chilies and garlic to your taste. Spread on bread and bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until cheese is melted and bubbly.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground chuck and chopped onion. Season to taste with garlic, cayenne pepper and salt. Drain off grease. In double boiler, cook Ro-Tel tomatoes and Velveeta cheese until melted. Crumble chips in casserole dish. Layer hamburger, cheese mixture, lettuce, tomatoes and Monterey Jack cheese. Eat and enjoy.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine butter and flour in a saucepan over low heat; gradually add chicken broth and milk, stirring constantly until smooth and thickened.
Stir in chicken, salt, pepper, mixed vegetables, and peas; mix well.
Pour into 13
x 9 x 2 inch baking dish.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Cream together flour and butter in double boiler until melted. Stir in milk slowly.
Stir constantly until thick.
Add cheese and pimento, salt and pepper; stir until smooth and cheese is melted.
Put drained asparagus into casserole, pour hot sauce over. Cover with buttered crumbs.
Bake in moderately hot oven until brown and bubbly.
This dish can be made and refrigerated before baking.

title: cheesy vegetable chowder
directions: Dice peppers, mince onion and mince garlic.
Saute in 2 sticks of margarine until vegetables are tender.
Sprinkle in flour and cook to a roux over low heat.
Cook roux.
Add milk over low heat; blend into mixture.
Add rest of ingredients except cheese.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly for approximately 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Dice cheese into big blocks; add to soup mixture, stirring until it is melted.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Mix butter and peanut butter in a large mixing bowl.
Blend well.
Add powdered sugar, small amounts at a time, until well mixed and mixture is consistency to make into small balls.
After mixture is shaped into balls, melt chocolate chips and paraffin in double boiler.
Dip balls into chocolate and let stand until dry. Balls may be rolled in coconut or crushed nuts.
Yield: 2 pounds.

title: potato candy
directions: Peel potatoes and mash in large mixing bowl.
Add sugar and vanilla gradually until mixture is of consistency of dough; roll out on waxed paper.
Spread generously with peanut butter; roll into log.
Chill for several hours or overnight.
Slice; store in refrigerator.
Rolls may be frozen.

title: chex ooey-chooey marshmallowey
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In large bowl, combine sugar, brown sugar, peanut butter, margarine, egg and vanilla extract until well blended; stir in cereal.
With a rubber spatula, spread mixture on ungreased pizza pan.
Bake 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle evenly with marshmallows and chocolate pieces.
Bake 7 to 10 minutes longer, until lightly browned.
Remove from oven and cool completely on wire rack.
Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours before cutting into 16 wedges.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator.

title: cocoa walnut brownie loaf with cocoa fudge frosting
directions: Cream margarine, sugars, vanilla and eggs until fluffy and light.
Combine dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture in thirds, alternating with yogurt.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 65 to 75 minutes.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly, blend with sugar, salt and vanilla. Gradually stir in scalded milk, pour into pie shell.
Bake for 25 or 30 minutes at 400°.

title: no-peek chicken
directions: Pour soup and milk over rice and mix.
Lay chicken breasts, thighs or legs over top of rice, skin up, to cover.
Sprinkle the soup mix over the chicken.
Cover pan lightly with foil and put in fridge overnight.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours in 9 x 3-inch pan.

title: hot spiced cider
directions: Simmer the cider, allspice, cinnamon and cloves for 20 minutes.
Add the lemon juice and orange juice.
Continue to simmer until ready to serve.
Add a small amount of light brown sugar if cider is not sweet enough.
Serves 10.

title: old favorite casserole
directions: Brown until done the beef, onion and green pepper. Drain.
Add tomato sauce, cheese and pepper.
Cook macaroni; drain.
Mix into sauce.
Put into 1 1/2-quart baking dish and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until bubbly.

title: polish country stew(bigos)
directions: Saute kielbasa in 1 tablespoon oil for 10 minutes.
Remove and place in casserole.
Add rest of oil to sausage drippings. Brown beef, pork, onions and mushrooms in oil for 15 minutes. Remove and add to casserole.
Drain kraut (reserving juice); rinse and add kraut, wine, tomato sauce, soy sauce, caraway seeds, bay leaves and garlic; mix well.
Add salt and pepper.
Cover and bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Stir every 30 minutes.
Add kraut juice if desired.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Dissolve the jello in the boiling water. Add the entire package of strawberries (no need to thaw them). Chill this mixture until it thickens.
Break up the angel cake into 1 1/2-inch chunks. Whip the cream until thick and fold into the gelatin mixture.
In a glass bowl, alternate layers of cake chunks and gelatin mixture until bowl is full. Cover and chill 12 hours. Top with Cool Whip before serving.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Blend crackers with butter.
Pat into pie tin.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Let butter stand at room temperature until softened.
In mixing bowl, cream the butter, shortening, brown sugar and granulated sugar.
Add the eggs and vanilla; beat well.
In a bowl, stir together the flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture and stir until well blended.
Stir in chocolate and nuts. Drop from a teaspoon 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Yields 6 dozen.

title: party potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until tender.
Beat sour cream, cream cheese and chives together.
Add hot potatoes and beat until smooth.
Add butter and salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into well-greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Dot with butter and sprinkle paprika on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: stuffed lettuce
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Stir in 1/4 cup mayonnaise, olives and onion.
Core lettuce; remove center, leaving 1-inch shell.
Fill with cheese mixture.
Wrap in foil.
Mix 1/2 cup mayonnaise with remaining ingredients.
Cover; chill lettuce and dressing overnight.
Cut lettuce into wedges.
Garnish salad plate with cucumbers, olives and dill pickle strips.
Serves 6.

title: stewed corn and tomatoes
directions: Score each row of kernels, then cut corn off of cob and scrape cob.
In a large saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer until vegetables are tender, stirring occasionally.
Serves 8.

title: spicy chicken
directions: Wash chicken in cold water; pat dry.
Place all ingredients in plastic bag and mix well.
Shake several pieces; be sure to coat evenly.
Heat 1/4 cup butter and 1/4 cup shortening; add chicken and brown.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until tender.

title: poor man's pie
directions: Combine oats, corn syrup, margarine, sugar and eggs.
Stir until blended.
Pour into unbaked pastry shell. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 50 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar, molasses and salt.
Boil on medium heat until 260° (very hard ball stage).
Pour over popped corn. Stir thoroughly while pouring syrup.
Butter hands lightly. Shape into balls.
Makes about 12 balls.

title: brown rice
directions: Melt margarine in large casserole dish.
Chop onion.
Add soups, water and rice.
Bake at 375° for about 1 hour, or until liquid cooks in.

title: cherry waldorf salad
directions: Bring 3/4 cup of apple juice to boil in medium saucepan. Dissolve cherry gelatin completely in boiling apple juice, stirring 2 minutes.
Mix remaining 1/2 cup apple juice and ice to measure 1 1/4 cups.
Add to gelatin, stirring until slightly thickened.
Remove any remaining ice.
Stir in fruit and celery. Spoon into individual dishes or serving bowl.
Refrigerate 2 hours or until firm.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all together.
Let it set a while.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Heat soup over medium heat, stirring until smooth.
Stir in all remaining ingredients until well blended.
Chill before serving.

title: baskin-robbins pie
directions: First Layer:
Melt oleo; stir in flour and nuts.
Pat in pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes; cool.

title: uncooked cucumber relish
directions: Chop vegetables fine and sprinkle with salt. Let stand 1 hour. Drain. Add sugar and vinegar. Stir well and bottle. Makes 8 pints.

title: orange mandarin salad
directions: Mix vanilla pudding, tapioca pudding, orange jello and boiling water together.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Cool and let set.
Add Cool Whip and oranges.
Mix together well.
Cool for several hours before serving.

title: crab salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Amounts of ingredients depends on size of salad desired.
Toss with herbed dill dressing.
(I add small amount of Ranch dressing.)

title: chicken purlow
directions: This is a full course meal in one dish; great for a cold winter night or a full blown gospel tent meeting.

title: milky way ice cream
directions: Dice all 6 candy bars.
Combine eggs, heavy cream, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Mix together and blend until creamy.
Pour into ice cream can (1 gallon).
Add sweetened condensed milk, sweet milk and candy pieces.
Fill ice cream can to the fill line with regular milk.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender; drain thoroughly.
Add remaining ingredients reserving half of crumbs for top.
Pour in casserole sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs over top.
Bake at 350° until bubbly!

title: french breakfast puffs
directions: Mix 1 teaspoon cinnamon and 1/2 cup sugar and set aside.
Cream shortening, 1/2 cup sugar and egg.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg.
Add to creamed mixture.
Alternate with milk, beating well after each addition.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately.
Dip in melted butter and then cinnamon sugar mixture until top is coated. Makes 12.

title: taco pizza
directions: Combine
hamburger
and taco seasoning mix.
Pour
over already prepared pizza crust.
Bake at 450°
for
minutes. When done, spread shredded lettuce, cut up tomato and shredded cheese on.	Serve with taco sauce, if desired.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cut up 1 cup berries.
Mix sugar and cornstarch in 2-quart saucepan.
Stir in 1 cup water gradually until smooth.
Add cut up berries.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thick and clear. Stir in a few drops of red food coloring.
Pour into baked pie crust and top with whipped cream.

title: cheese and potato casserole
directions: Allow hash browns to thaw.
Combine hash browns, onion dip and half of cheese.
Add 1/4 cup of melted margarine.
Mix. Spoon into large casserole dish.
Pour remaining 1/4 cup of margarine over top of casserole.
Add remaining cheese.
Sprinkle Ritz crackers over the top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: salmon loaf(appetizer)
directions: Flake salmon and remove skin and bones.
Mix remaining ingredients except pecans and parsley.
Mix well and chill. Prepare pecans.
Chop fine and mix with parsley on wax paper. Shape salmon in desired shape.
Roll in pecans.
Chill.
Garnish with black olives.
Serve with crackers.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift together the dry ingredients.
Add all the rest; mix. Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 1/2 sheet cake or a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: garlic parmesan bread sticks
directions: In mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in water; then add sugar.
Let set 5 minutes.
Add 1/2 c. butter, salt, and 2 c. flour; beat until smooth.
Stir in remaining flour to form a soft dough.
Let rise until doubled in size (about 45 min.).
Punch down dough and turn onto a floured surface.
Roll into a 24X10 inch rectangle.
Cut in half lengthwise and then into 5X1 inch strips.
Twist each strip and place one inch apart on greased sheets.
Brush with remaining butter, sprinkle with garlic and parmesan.
Cover and let rise for 20 minutes.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20-30 minutes.
Serve with warm sauce.

title: strawberry jello dessert
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Mix in frozen strawberries. Refrigerate until thick, but not set.

title: champagne salad
directions: Blend sugar and cream cheese well.
Drain pineapple and strawberries.
Add fruits to cream mixture.
Add Cool Whip; refrigerate 1 hour.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Prepare rice as directed and combine.
Saute mushrooms, green pepper, onion and celery in butter.
Add rice and all remaining ingredients.
Place in casserole.

title: deep dish hamburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown meat and onion; stir in seasonings, beans and soup.
Put in casserole dish.
Put mashed potatoes on top (or mix in rice).
Top with cheese and bake about 30 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix together and serve with vegetables.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients.
Add fruit.
Refrigerate fruit before mixing or mix then refrigerate.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream the cream cheese and margarine.
Add sugar to cream cheese, then alternately add flour and eggs.
Beat until mixed. Add extracts and mix; pour in greased and floured tube pan.
Put in cold oven and turn on to 325°.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours.

title: craisin bark
directions: Over medium heat, melt chocolate in double boiler or melt in microwave-safe 2-quart bowl for about 2 minutes on High or until melted. Remove from heat; stir in craisins, Rice Krispies and nuts. Mix well. Pour onto wax-lined cookie sheet and spread to desired thickness. Cool until set. Break up in pieces. Store in airtight container.

title: ice cream sandwich dessert
directions: Put a layer of ice cream sandwiches in 9 x 13 pan (ungreased).
Spread 1/2 carton of whipped topping over bars. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup peanuts.
Drizzle with 3/4 jar of topping. Put another layer of ice cream bars.
Spread remainder of whipped topping.
Sprinkle with remainder of peanuts.
Drizzle with rest of chocolate topping.
Freeze, will keep in freezer for several months.

title: lenny's zucchini casserole
directions: Slice zucchini 1/4-inch thick.
Fry beef and onion; drain.
Add garlic, salt, pepper and uncooked rice.
Line casserole with 1/2 the beef and 1/2 the zucchini.
Mix together the soup and cottage cheese.
Put 1/2 over beef and zucchini.
Layer the rest of beef and zucchini; top with remaining soup mix.
Top with grated cheese. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook beans and drain.
Melt oleo; add flour and cook over low heat until thickened.
Remove from heat; stir in sugar, onion, mustard and sour cream.
Fold mixture in beans.
Place in 2-quart casserole; sprinkle with cheese.
Top with croutons.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pastel de yuca
directions: Peel and boil "yuca" (potatoes) in salted water until tender. Mash while still hot with a fork, add egg, butter and salt.
Take 3/4 of mixture and coat bottom and sides of Pyrex dish.
Put aside.
Fry onion, green pepper, garlic, coriander and ground beef in a casserole; add chopped tomato and season with salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook 10 minutes.
Spoon filling into Pyrex dish and cover with the rest of the "yuca" mixture.
Bake at 350° until golden. Serve hot.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Pour into casserole dish; sprinkle remaining 1/2 package cheese.
Layer cooked stuffing over mixture. Bake 50 minutes at 350°.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: quick sausage and rice casserole(working family)
directions: Brown sausage in microwave.
Combine rest of ingredients. Stir well.
Put noodles on top.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes, covered.
Kids love this!

title: cornbread salad
directions: Prepare cornbread according to package.
Cool and crumble into large container.
Add the next 5 ingredients to cornbread. Combine creamy cucumber dressing and mayonnaise.
Add to cornbread mixture and stir well.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: strawberry congealed salad
directions: Dissolve strawberry jello in boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries and blend until berries are thawed, then mix the drained pineapple and pecans.
Pour half of the mixture in flat dish and refrigerate until it has jelled.
Whip together the sour cream and cream cheese until well blended and spread on top of jello.
Then make a third layer with the other half of jello mix and chill.

title: never-fail meringue
directions: Mix cold water and starch.
Add to boiling water; cook until thick.
Add slowly to beaten egg whites and sugar.
Beat until stiff but not dry.
Meringue doesn't weep.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Mix last three ingredients and pour over oyster crackers. Stir every 10 minutes for 2 hours.

title: venison pot roast
directions: Lay roast on aluminum foil.
Sprinkle with soup mix and dot with butter.
Wrap tightly in foil.
Bake 3 hours in a 300° oven or until meat is tender.
Remove roast to hot platter.
Rinse foil with remaining 1/4 cup of wine to pick up juices and pour over meat.
Serve immediately with buttered noodles as a side dish.

title: chocolate syrup
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Add sugar, chocolate chips, salt and vanilla.
Stir until melted and add evaporated milk.
Boil and keep stirring for about 5 minutes.

title: sofrito
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender and puree until it has a smooth sauce like consistency, adding 1 tablespoon of vegetable oil while pureeing.

title: holiday brew
directions: Combine all ingredients in a Dutch oven; bring to a boil. Remove from heat, and discard cinnamon sticks.
Serve hot.
Yields about 1 1/2 quarts.
Beverage may be stored in the refrigerator and reheated.

title: dawn's famous pasta salad
directions: Rinse pasta in cold water.
Add all ingredients except cheese. Add 1 to 1 1/2 bottles of dressing.
Stir all ingredients. Refrigerate overnight.
Serve next day with cheese added in.
Test taste to determine if you need more dressing.
This tastes better the longer it is refrigerated and dressing soaks in.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Melt butter on bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle crumbs over butter.
Sprinkle nuts over crumbs.
Scatter chocolate, then butterscotch pieces.
Sprinkle coconut over the pieces.
Pour sweetened condensed milk.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: freezer bread cinnamon rolls
directions: Let loaf of bread dough thaw.
Roll out on floured board real thin.
Spread with butter.
Sprinkle the brown sugar over the butter.
Roll up jelly roll fashion.
Cut into 12 slices.
Let rise 6 hours or overnight in a greased round bread pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until light brown.

title: butterhorn rolls
directions: Scald milk, then combine shortening, sugar and salt.
Set aside until lukewarm.
Add yeast, stir.
Add eggs, then flour. Mix until it feels elastic like, pliable.
Turn out onto a floured service and kneed until you feel bubbles crackling between your fingers.
Grease a bowl and put the dough into it, turn it over so the greased side will be up.
Cover and let rise until doubled in size.
Cut into 3 wedges, then roll out in a pie shape, butter, then cut like pie slices.
Roll big side to small side.
Then place on baking sheet.
Cover and let rise until double again. Bake at 425 for 8 minutes or until golden brown.
Brush with butter as soon as they come out of the oven.

title: crunchy peanut butter balls
directions: Heat raisins and apple juice concentrate in a saucepan.
Boil about 2 minutes.
Pour raisins in a blender and puree.
Mix raisin puree and remainder of ingredients in a bowl.
If dry, add a few drops of water.
Shape the mixture into small balls.
Refrigerate overnight.
Yields 30 small balls.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown beef and put in a 9 x 13-inch dish; cut onion and press into top of meat.
Add Tater Tots on top of meat and onion.
Mix soup and milk in small bowl and drizzle over ingredients.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: snitchbrot
directions: Put fruit in 2 quarts of water and bring to simmer to soften fruit.
Pour liquid into a large bowl.
Add sugar, molasses and spices to the warm liquid.
Add flour until a soft dough is formed.
Let cool to lukewarm so you don't kill yeast.
Add yeast and fruit.
Let rise in a warm place until it doubles.
Knead lightly and separate to pans.
Hand shaped loaves will also work. Let dough rise and double again.
Then bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Makes 5 to 10 loaves depending on size of pan.

title: pudding frosting
directions: Whip at high speed.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter, oil, sugar and eggs.
Blend thoroughly.
Sift together flour, soda, cream of tartar and salt.
Mix into creamed mixture.
Add vanilla.
Mix well.

title: glazed carrots and onions
directions: Peel carrots and cut into quarters.
Slice onions.
In a large saucepan, combine 2 of the bouillon cubes with carrots.
Add boiling water to cover, stir and dissolved bouillon cubes.
Cover and cook for 10 minutes.
Add onions and cook 5 minutes longer. Drain.
In large skillet, melt butter; add remaining bouillon cube and sugar.
Stir until cube is dissolved.
Add vegetables.
Cook until golden brown, stirring frequently.
Serves 4.

title: roasted asparagus
directions: Coat asparagus with oil.
Sprinkle with a little kosher salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Preheat oven to 425° and cook for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: pelangoche tacos
directions: Fry bacon and meat until done.
Add remainder of ingredients except cheese and simmer 10 minutes.
Top with cheese until melted.
Heat tortillas in dry pan.
Fold ingredients in hot tortillas and eat (may want to add salsa).
Serves 6 to 8 tacos.

title: pineapple-orange punch
directions: Mix the juices.
Divide the sherbet into 6 tall glasses; add the juice. Stir.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream the shortening, peanut butter and sugars together.
Add egg and beat.
Sift remaining dry ingredients into small bowl.
Add both together and vanilla.
Form into small balls.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: liver paste(leverposteg)
directions: Put liver and fat through meat grinder about 5 times.
In a medium skillet, melt butter and add flour to blend.
Add milk and cook until smooth.
Add this sauce to liver mixture.
Add eggs, chopped onion and spices.
Beat mixture well.
Bake in a loaf pan set in a pan of shallow water for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°. Cool and serve on rye bread or crackers.

title: puritans' punch
directions: Blend 1 1/2 quarts ice cream into hot coffee. Chill until time to serve. Add soda water and float 1/2 quart ice cream.
When serving, spoon a little ice cream into each cup.
Makes approximately 4 dozen cups.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla, salt and soda. Mix well.
Add flour and mix well.
Stir in oats.
Mix well.
Roll into 3 long tubes and wrap in waxed paper.
Refrigerate 2 hours or overnight.
When ready to preheat oven to 300°, slice thinly and bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 22 to 25 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: party ice cream bombe
directions: Chill 7 cup mold or Bundt pan in freezer for 1 hour.
Pour melted margarine onto cookie crumbs and moisten.
Press into chilled mold around sides and bottom.
Freeze for 1/2 hour. Quickly spread softened vanilla ice cream over crumbs with a spatula or spoon back on inside of mold about 1-inch thick.
Return to freezer 30 to 45 minutes to harden.
Repeat with mint and sherbet.
Put lime sherbet in center to fill mold.
Freeze 2 hours or overnight.
Unmold.
Turn onto chilled plate.
Center can be filled with fruit.
Slice and enjoy.

title: coffee cake
directions: Stir all ingredients together and spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix, then beat on medium speed for 4 minutes.
Pour in 10-inch tube pan lined with paper on bottom. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tester in center comes out clean and cake pulls away from side of pan.
Do not underbake. Cool in pan 15 minutes.

title: chocolate wacky cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients in
a large mixing bowl.
Make a well. Add oil, vinegar, cold water
and vanilla.
Mix at medium speed until well blended.
Bake in a greased cake pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots until done, but firm.
Drain and cool.
Mix together other ingredients.
Add carrots.
Cover and marinate at least 12 hours.
Stir once or twice.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Melt oleo in frypan and brown onion and mushrooms.
Stir in flour, salt, pepper and poultry seasoning.
Cook until bubbly. Slowly add broth, then the cream and stir until the mixture begins to boil.
Add chicken.
Butter a 1 1/2 or 2-quart casserole dish. Place a layer of rice on bottom of dish.
Cover with half the mixture.
Repeat.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake in preheated oven at 400° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.
Turkey may be used in place of chicken.

title: cheese cake
directions: Combine ingredients as above.
Pour into shell of graham cracker crumbs as for a pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour (until firm and browned).
For pineapple cheese cake, add 1/2 cup crushed pineapple, drained.

title: helen's dirty rice
directions: Boil livers, necks and gizzards in 4 cups water.
Cook on low until tender.
Add bay leaves and seasoning salt to stock.
When done, remove chicken from stock.
Let cool.
Chop liver, neck and gizzards very fine.
Save stock.
Saute vegetables in 1 tablespoon oil.
Cook 2 cups rice as usual.
Add parsley and green onions to rice.
Add sauteed vegetables, necks, livers and gizzards to stock and simmer for 30 minutes.
Season with low-fat margarine instead of oil.
Add sage, thyme and red pepper to stock.
Add rice; turn fire off.
Let set a few minutes before serving.

title: hot and sour soup
directions: Heat chicken broth to boiling.
Add pork strips, bamboo shoots, Woodear (drained), bean curd and mushrooms.
Return to boiling and add salt, soy sauce, sugar, white pepper, red pepper sauce and vinegar, stirring all along.
Continue boiling for a total cooking time of 20 minutes.
Stir in cornstarch mixture and keep stirring until soup is thickened.
Pour beaten eggs gently over the top.
Turn off the heat and stir eggs gently into soup. Add sesame oil.
Spoon into bowls and serve topped with chopped green onions, if desired.

title: quick party bars
directions: Cream margarine.
Add light brown sugar.
Add vanilla and egg; beat until light and creamy.
Add flour.
Fold in oatmeal.
(No baking powder in recipe.)

title: easy corn pudding
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and salt and pepper in blender.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° until set, about 30 to 60 minutes.

title: sensational strawberry bread with strawberry butter
directions: Place yeast in 2 cups warm (not hot) water.
Melt butter; add to sugar in large bowl.
Add beaten egg and dissolved yeast mixture.
Add flour and stir until thoroughly mixed.
To cook, drop by spoonfuls into well-greased muffin tin (or use cupcake papers) and bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until brown.

title: mandarin orange sweet sour nutty salad
directions: In a salad bowl, combine lettuce, oranges, parsley, celery and onions.
Shake together oil, vinegar, salt, pepper, 2 tablespoons sugar and Tabasco sauce.

title: baked tomatoes
directions: Cut thin slices from top of each tomato.
Hollow out slightly. Combine salad oil, sugar, onions, salt, mustard, vinegar and Worcestershire sauce.
Spoon into center of each tomato.
Combine cracker crumbs and butter.
Sprinkle over top of tomatoes.
Place in 9-inch pie plate or shallow baking dish.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: caroline's italian meatballs
directions: Soak bread in water for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add eggs and mix well.
mix with ground beef, Parmesan cheese, parsley, salt, oregano and pepper.
With wet hands, form meat mixture into small balls.
Brown slowly in hot oil.
Add meatballs to sauce.
Simmer loosely covered
for 30 minutes.
(Can also bake meatballs on a cookie sheet in 350° oven for 20 minutes.)

title: pasta salad
directions: Cut pepperoni and Cheddar cheese into small chunks. Blend all ingredients together in a large bowl. Refrigerate and serve cold.

title: amazing coconut pie
directions: Combine milk, sugar, biscuit mix, eggs, butter and vanilla in electric blender container.
Cover and blend on low speed for 3 minutes.
Pour into greased 9 in. pie pan.
Let stand about 5 minutes, then sprinkle with coconut.
Bake at 350 degrees about 40 minutes.
Serve warm or cool.
This pie makes its own crust.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Warm tortillas in oven by placing on a baking sheet, covering with moist dish towel. Heat at 250° for 10 minutes. Combine yogurt, soup, and chiles. Set aside. Spread 1/4 c. chicken in middle of tortilla, sprinkle about 1 Tbsp. cheese, roll up tortilla and place in a 9 x 13 inch baking dish.
