When all tortillas have been filled and rolled, pour yogurt mixture over all tortillas. Sprinkle with remaining cheese. Bake uncovered at 350° for 20 minutes or until hot but not bubbling. This freezes very well. Just reheat in microwave until hot.

title: cole slaw
directions: Stir vinegar into real mayonnaise; then blend in salt, sugar, pepper and grated onion.
Chill until just before serving. Combine cabbage, carrot and green pepper; toss with mayonnaise. Mix until well coated.
Makes about 8 to 10 servings.

title: giant guppy cookie
directions: Mix dough. Let chill for 1 hour. Roll out dough 1/4-inch thickness. Cut in shape of Guppy Clown head. Put big nose of dough on. Cook 10 to 12 minutes at 350°. Decorate with colored frosting.

title: cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage and carrots fine.
Chop onion small.
Mix dressing ingredients all together and pour over chopped ingredients.
Stir well.
Best if set overnight.
Stir every couple hours.
Makes 96 (2 1/4 ounce) servings.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix ingredients together. Salt to taste. Marinate overnight.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown beef and onion in butter.
Combine all other ingredients and simmer.
Serve over buns.

title: fruit squares
directions: Cream sugar and margarine together.
Add other ingredients and mix well until blended.
Spread out in a greased and floured cookie sheet.
Make indentations of 24 squares with a knife.
Drop a spoonful of fruit filling into the center of each square.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool and cut into 24 squares.
Sprinkle with 4x sugar if you want.

title: pork chops barbecue
directions: Put chops in pan and pour sauce over.
Bake at 320° for 30 minutes.
Turn chops and pour more sauce over.
Bake 1 hour and 30 minutes more, uncovered.
Double for 6 chops.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except bread crumbs and 1/2 stick margarine.
Place in greased casserole dish.
Combine bread crumbs and 1/2 stick margarine, melted.
Put on top.
Bake in 275° oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until brown.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: mike's mac(adapted from an old navy recipe)
directions: You will need a hefty appetite.

title: chocolate chip cookie squares
directions: Combine sugar, butter, brown sugar and vanilla in a small bowl. Beat until creamy. Beat in eggs. Gradually add flour.
Stir in chocolate chips. Spread into greased baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Combine peanuts, sugar and corn syrup in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish; microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Add butter and vanilla; blend well.
Microwave again for 4 more minutes.
Stir and microwave an additional 2 minutes.
Peanuts should be light brown in color and syrup very hot.
Slowly add baking soda; stir gently until light and foamy.
Pour entire mixture into a lightly greased pizza pan.
Let cool for 30 minutes and serve.

title: very best brownies(cakelike and a tad chewy)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large mixer bowl, combine the melted butter, sugar and cocoa.
Add the eggs, one at a time, blending after each.
Add the remaining ingredients and mix just until combined.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch glass dish and bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until the top is firm to the touch. Do not overbake as the brownies will be dry.
Allow to stand 15 minutes, then cut into squares.
Can be frosted but if so, do it while brownies are still hot.

title: chinese-style beef, broccoli and rice
directions: With a sharp knife, cut steak diagonally across the grain into thin slices.
In a medium bowl, mix together ginger, soy sauce, sugar and cornstarch. Add meat strips and toss to mix well.
Leave set for 5 to 10 minutes.
In a 10-inch skillet, heat oil over high heat until hot.

Add meat mixture. Cook, stirring over high heat, until meat loses its redness, 4 to 5 minutes. Remove to a plate. Add water, rice and broccoli to skillet and heat to boiling. Reduce heat to medium-low. Cover and simmer 5 to 6 minutes or until broccoli is tender.
Return meat to skillet and heat to boiling, stirring often. Simmer, stirring, 1 minute.
Serves 4.

title: chicken salad pie
directions: Combine ingredients and pour in pie shell.

title: easy heavenly hash fudge(microwave recipe)
directions: Slice margarine or butter into a bowl.
Add milk and cocoa. Cook on Full power for 2 minutes.
Stir in sugar; beat until smooth.
Add vanilla and nuts; cook on Full power for 30 seconds. Beat.
Add marshmallows and pour out into buttered dish.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: french lasagne
directions: Cook spinach and noodles as directed on package and brown meat. Butter pan, line with noodles, spinach, meat, Mozzarella cheese, noodles, meat, spinach and Mozzarella cheese.
Heat mushroom soup, milk and seasonings.
Pour over all.
Pour tomato sauce on top. Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and pepper.
Drain off excess fat. Cook macaroni; drain.
In dish, add all of the ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Top with cheese.
Return to oven and let cheese melt.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar, Karo and hot water.
Bring to a boil and add peanuts.
Cook on medium heat.
Let cook until peanuts start popping. Cook for 1 minute longer. Add butter while on low heat. Stir in soda until it turns yellow.
Pour on greased pan.
Let cool and break into pieces.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients in pan and bake at 350° until set, approximately 45 minutes.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Place ground beef in casserole dish.
Add corn, cream of chicken soup and onion. Mix well.
Spread evenly across bottom of dish.
Place Tater Tots on top.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from oven, place slices of cheese on top.
Place in oven and melt.
Remove and let cool.

title: cantaloupe breakfast soup
directions: Quarter melon; remove and discard seeds.
Cut fruit from rind. Dice fruit and place into a food processor or blender.
Add orange and lime juices; puree.
Place yogurt in a glass mixing bowl and beat with a whisk until light and smooth.
Whisk in melon mixture.
Cover bowl and refrigerate for at least three hours. Serve cold, sprinkled with fresh mint leaves and slivers of melon. Serves 4.

title: fudgies
directions: Mix together sugar, cocoa, milk and salt in a heavy pan. Bring to a rolling boil, stirring constantly and let boil for 1 minute, stirring.
Remove from heat and add quickly the butter, peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir until melted, then add oats.
Dip into cupcake papers or onto wax paper about cookie size amounts. Let cool and enjoy.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Smash ground beef out in pan.
Put soups over meat.
Cover with cheese.
Cover with Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Brown bacon; drain. Saute chopped scallions in bacon grease. Set grease aside. Clean broccoli and cut into small pieces (with or without stems). Add chopped apples, bacon, raisins, nuts and scallions. Mix some bacon grease with Ranch dressing and pour over salad. Mix thoroughly; add salt and pepper to taste. Refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.

title: cooked apples
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 4-quart Dutch oven; bring to a boil over medium-high heat.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Yields about 5 1/2 cups.

title: chinese cabbage salad
directions: Brown noodles and almonds lightly in small amount of oil. Cool.

title: almond horns
directions: Roll into balls; roll each ball into rope shapes.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes on a greased cookie sheet.

title: baked chicken salad
directions: Mix all together (but the potato chips) carefully.
If it appears too dry or stiff, add 1/2 cup broth.
Place in flat dish and cover with crushed potato chips.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Will serve 6 to 8.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix together yellow cake mix, butter or margarine and 1 eggs. Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
(Mixture is very thick.
Add small amount of water to help spread.)

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Butter casserole (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Set oven at 350°.
Saute green onions lightly.
Add soup and milk.
Mix. Remove from stove. Layer half the potatoes in casserole, then all the cheese, then another layer of potatoes.
Pour soup mixture over all.
Cover with aluminum foil for 1 hour.
Uncover and cook 30 more minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: quick and easy chicken pot pie
directions: Drain vegetables. Mix chicken, soup and onion with vegetables. Season to taste. Pour into crust. Cover with other crust, mashing edges together to seal. With point of knife, make several holes in top crust. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, until golden brown.

title: pudding dessert
directions: Crust:
Mix flour, margarine and pecans.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.

title: spiced oyster crackers
directions: Combine dry Hidden Valley, oil, dill weed, garlic powder and lemon pepper or juice.
Mix well.
Pour over crackers.
Stir to coat.
Put in flat pan in warm oven at 200° for 15 to 20 minutes. Stir once or twice.
Store in covered container.

title: green bean almondine
directions: In large skillet brown almonds in 2 teaspoons butter 3 to 4 minutes until golden; set aside.
In same skillet saute green beans in remaining butter 5 to 8 minutes until crisp-tender.
Stir in lemon juice and pepper.
Add salt to taste.
Sprinkle almonds over beans.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream the butter and sugar; add beaten egg, lemon juice and well mashed bananas.
Add flour, sifted with salt, baking powder and baking soda, then add the broken nuts.
Turn into a greased loaf pan and bake in a moderate oven at 350°.
Slice thin and spread with cream cheese (optional).

title: split pea soup(microwave)
directions: Soak peas in 1 1/2 quarts water overnight.
Drain.
Combine peas and remaining ingredients in a 4-quart casserole.
Season with salt and pepper as desired.
Cook, covered, on Full power for 20 to 30 minutes or until boiling.
Stir halfway through cooking time.
Continue cooking on Cook level 4 for 10 to 15 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Stir several times during cooking time.
If desired, remove and mash 2 cups of cooked peas.
Return to soup and blend.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Mix together and let stand for 2 hours.

title: jalapeno black-eyed pea casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender.
Add ground beef and brown.
Stir in jalapeno black-eyed peas, rice and tomatoes.
Mix well; spoon mixture into a 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until cheese is melted. Serves 6 or 8.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and beat until fluffy.
Add flour and flavoring.
Mix thoroughly, then add 7-Up.
Stir in slowly.
Cook in deep pan for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars; add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well. Add sifted dry ingredients, oats and nuts; mix well.
(Add chocolate chips and spices here, if desired.)
Roll in balls the size of walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet immediately after removing from oven.

title: crunchy ham salad(or chicken)
directions: Mix and chill.
Just before serving, add 1 1/2 cups shoestring potatoes.

title: easy yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve sugar and yeast in water.
Add salt, oil and egg.
Add about 5 1/2 cups flour (just sift into mixture; dough will be sticky).
Pat dough onto floured board; cut and dip into butter. Fold.
Let rise 1 1/2 hours.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Makes 25 rolls.
This dough will hold in refrigerator for 3 days.

title: sour cream porridge(served at international night)
directions: Boil the sour cream, covered, for 2 minutes.
Add half the flour and stir carefully to bring the butter to the surface. (Does not always happen.)
Skim it off and keep warm.
Stir in the rest of the flour and add the milk.
Simmer the porridge for 5 to 6 minutes.
Salt to taste.

title: unbaked cookie treat
directions: Combine
in saucepan butter, sugar, cocoa, dry milk and water. Mix well and let come to a rolling boil for 3 minutes. Remove from
heat;
add
peanut butter and vanilla; mix well. Gradually add
rolled
oats and mix well.
Drop on waxed paper or greased pans.
Makes like a fudge.

title: fiery hot shrimp
directions: Wash, peel and devein shrimp.
Place shrimp shells in a 2 quart saucepan; add
1/4 onion and a stalk of celery.
Cover with water.
Bring to
a boil; reduce heat and simmer about 35 minutes. Strain and
set
aside.
This
is
your shrimp stock you'll need.

title: lima bean bake
directions: Boil beans until soft.
Saute onion and celery with Pam.
In a large baking dish, mix all ingredients, except tomato sauce and bacon.
Pour tomato sauce over mixture in baking dish and top with bacon strips.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: onion potatoes
directions: Layer potatoes and onions; salt and pepper and put butter on top.
Bake until tender on grill in foil.

title: bacon cornsticks
directions: Fry bacon until crisp. Drain and cool on paper towels. Reserve 1/4 cup drippings. Crumble bacon and set aside.
In medium bowl, stir and toss flour, cornmeal, sugar, baking powder and salt. Set aside. In small bowl, whisk milk, egg, corn kernels and bacon drippings until blended.

Add to dry ingredients along with crumbled bacon and stir until blended. Spoon into buttered cornstick pans, filling each mold 2/3 full. Bake in preheated 400° oven about 15 minutes until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in pans for 3 minutes, then invert to remove. Makes 7 cornsticks.

title: tomato jam
directions: Scald and peel tomatoes, then quarter them.
Place in pan and add sugar, vinegar and spices. Cook slowly until thickened and put in jars.

title: halunski
directions: Note:
The amount of ingredients depends on how much you care to make and size of the cabbage head.

title: lemon spongettes
directions: Cream the shortening, sugar and flour together.
Add egg yolks, milk and flavoring.
Mix.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Cook in cups in water about 40 minutes at 300°.
May be doubled.
May be cooked in one flat pan and cut into portions.

title: typical new england strawberry-rhubarb jam
directions: Mix rhubarb with pineapple, strawberries and sugar.
Let stand for 30 minutes.
Place in saucepan.
Bring to a boil and cook for 12 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add gelatin and stir.
Pour into sterilized jars and seal.
Makes about 3 to 4 pints.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli 5 minutes.
Drain and place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Drizzle with 4 tablespoons melted margarine. Sprinkle with 1 cup of the cheese.
Mix soup, onion and mayonnaise and spread over broccoli and cheese.
Add the Pepperidge Farm dressing, then sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Cover dish with foil and bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: overnight lettuce salad
directions: Layer first 6 ingredients in a dish. Spread mayonnaise on top. Sprinkle with sugar, then cheese and bacon bits. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Toss when ready to serve.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together; add raisins, milk and shortening.
Mix well and knead the dough on a floured surface. (The more kneading, the better.)
Place in a well-greased, 1-inch deep baking pan and bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: craft clay
directions: Combine together.
Cook until thickened to dough-like consistency.
Turn mixture out on pastry board and knead.
Cover with damp cloth or keep in plastic bag.

title: lemon fluff blueberry pie
directions: Wash berries and drain; spread on towel to dry.
Beat milk; add lemon juice and beat again.
Add beaten egg yolks.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold in mixture.
Gently pour in berries. Place in pie shell.
Toast to a light brown.

title: spam casserole
directions: Cook onions in butter.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put in casserole dish.
Top with slices of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix peanuts,
sugar
and syrup in iron skillet and cook until light
brown
in
color.
Peanuts
will
begin
to	pop. Remove from fire
and add 1 teaspoon soda and 1 teaspoon salt. Stir quickly and pour on buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Break into small pieces when cool.

title: u. s. senate bean soup
directions: Rinse beans in cold water. Check carefully for rocks and pebbles and cover with water. Soak at least 8 hours or overnight. Drain and return beans to pot. Cover with 5-inches of water. Finely chop onions, celery, garlic and carrots and add to pot. Add ham and remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil; reduce heat and add water as needed or it will burn. Keep beans covered with water at all times and stir often. Season to taste. Soup is best when prepared a day ahead of time and reheated.

title: tarragon chicken with carrots and linguine
directions: Cook linguine until tender.
Drain.
In large skillet, heat stock over medium heat.
Cut chicken into strips 1/2-inch wide and 3-inches long; add to stock.
Cook 7 minutes.
Add carrots, mushrooms, parsley and tarragon.
Heat until chicken is cooked through, about 5 minutes.
Add linguine and toss.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cocoa, cinnamon, eggs and soda in large bowl.
Heat margarine and water to a boil.
Add to dry ingredients; mix well.
Add buttermilk and vanilla.
Mix well. Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased pan and bake about 20 minutes in 400° oven.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Set oven at 375°.
Sift flour and measure.
Add baking soda and salt; sift again.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add beaten egg, peanut butter and vanilla.
Form into small balls and place on cookie sheet.
Then flatten balls by making crisscrosses with a fork.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Makes approximately 70 cookies.

title: tuna bake
directions: Brown onions and pepper in butter.
Add salt and flour and blend well.
Add soup and milk, stirring until a thin sauce has formed.
Add tuna and lemon juice.
Pour into a greased 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6.
I serve this over toast or with corn bread.

title: jolly boy doughnuts
directions: In a saucepan, beat eggs. Add milk and heat together.
Add vanilla. Remove from heat.
In a bowl, mix dry ingredients together.
Add to egg mixture. Add shortening. Drop by teaspoonfuls in hot fat.
Cook until brown.
These will turn themselves.

title: impossible chocolate cream pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine all ingredients in a blender and blend on high for 1 minute. Pour into a greased 9-inch pie plate. Bake for 30 minutes or until set. Cool completely before serving. Serve topped with whipped cream, nuts, cherries or chocolate sprinkles.

title: meringues
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Beat egg whites with all ingredients but sugar until soft peaks form.
Add sugar gradually until it is dissolved.
Put spoonfuls of mixture on brown paper on cookie sheet.
Build up sides slightly if meringues are to be filled (with, for example, ice cream or whipped cream).
Put in oven. Turn it off and leave meringues for 2 to 3 hours.
Makes about 2 dozen 3-inch meringues.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Slice rolls in half.
Mix rest of ingredients.
Place a scant tablespoon of cheese mixture on each half.
Bake as directed on package.
Makes about 20 puffs.

title: banana bread(banana nut bread)
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and egg together.
Add the mashed bananas and mix thoroughly.
Add flour, soda and salt and again mix thoroughly.
Lastly, add the chopped nuts, if desired.
Pour batter into greased and floured bread pan and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cranberry tea
directions: Cook the first 5 ingredients for 10 minutes; do not let boil. Remove from heat.
Add the pineapple-orange juice and lemon juice (optional).
Store in refrigerator.
Serve hot or cold.

title: apple brownies
directions: Mix margarine and sugar; beat eggs and add to sugar mixture. Stir in flour, baking soda and baking powder.
Cut up apples.
Add apples and walnuts to batter.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cheese ball recipe
directions: Make into ball.
Chill
until
firm.
Then
add chopped pecans until well covered.
Keep in refrigerator.
Take out of refrigerator about 1 hour before serving.

title: harvest vegetable sauce
directions: Prepare pasta conventionally as package directs.
Drain and keep warm.
Meanwhile, in a 2 1/2-quart casserole, cook carrots and next 7 ingredients, covered, on High in microwave until almost tender.
Stir twice during cooking.
Add mushrooms; cook, covered, 4 to 6 minutes, until tender, stirring once during cooking.
Toss mixture with pasta and vinegar or lemon juice.
If you like, sprinkle with chopped, fresh basil or parsley.
Makes 4 servings.

title: brownies
directions: Melt chocolate with fat in saucepan over low heat.
Add sugar and blend.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased pan. Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Cut into squares while hot.

title: banana bars
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Mix milk, soda, bananas and vanilla.
Add to mixture alternately with flour (1/3 at a time).
Add chopped nuts.
Pour into 8 1/2 x 11-inch pan or two 8-inch pans, greased and floured.
Set aside.

title: cranberry wine punch
directions: In punch bowl, combine all ingredients.
Add ice ring and garnish with sliced orange and fresh strawberries.
Serves 15 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: blender cheesecake
directions: Pour sour cream, eggs, sugar, lemon juice and vanilla into blender.
Blend until smooth.
Cut cream cheese into 1-inch cubes. Add to mixture while blender is going.
Blend until smooth.
Pour into crusts.

title: dan's fruit dressing
directions: Mix above ingredients and drizzle over fresh cut fruit before serving.

title: andy's easy spaghetti
directions: Brown beef. Drain. Saute onion with beef. Combine all other ingredients and serve over spaghetti noodles.

title: cherried cranberries
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and bring them to a boil over medium heat.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Cool them (still covered).
Serve them for Thanksgiving or any other holiday in place of canned cranberry sauce.

title: lemon oat lacies
directions: Beat margarine and sugar until creamy.
Add remaining ingredients, except powdered sugar.
Mix well.
Cover and chill at least 30 minutes.
Heat oven to 350°.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with bottom of glass dipped in powdered sugar.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until edges are brown.
Cool and sprinkle with a little more sugar.

title: scrumptious whole wheat bread
directions: Bring 1 1/2 cups water to a boil and pour over cracked wheat. Let cool.

title: mom bamber's veal marsala
directions: Marinate veal cutlets in 1/4 cup of Marsala wine for 1 hour; remove from marinade and dust cutlets in flour.
In skillet, saute garlic in olive oil.
Over medium heat, add veal cutlets and brown on both sides.
Remove cutlets and keep warm.
Drain oil from skillet.
Add butter and remaining Marsala to skillet and cook to reduce.
Return cutlets to skillet, spooning Marsala sauce over them.
Season with salt and pepper as desired.
Serve sprinkled with chopped parsley or green onion.

title: magic fruit cake for christmas
directions: Mix together in a large mixing bowl.
Line a tube pan with wax paper.
Pour mixture into pan and bake at 250° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: Mix all together; cook until thick and cool.
Then pour into baked pie shell.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix cocoa and cornstarch in 1/3 to 1/2 cup of water until smooth. Mix other items in with this. Cook at 350° for 40 minutes. This will make 2 deep-dish or 3 shallow dish pies.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Add first 5 ingredients to chicken stock and cook until tender; thicken and put in cake pan (9 x 12-inch).
Use pie crust on bottom and Bisquick on top.
Bake at 350° until brown and bubbly.
Yields 6 servings.

title: sour cream nut coffee cake
directions: Cream 1/2 cup butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs one at a time.
Beat well after each.
Blend flour, baking powder and baking soda.
Add to creamed mixture, alternating with sour cream. Spread half in a 10-inch tube (angel food) pan, greased and floured.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs.
Combine salt and flour. Add alternately with milk, mixing after each addition.
Stir in vanilla and lemon.
Bake at 325° or 1 hour or so.

title: mexican dip
directions: Mix all together night before.
Serve with nacho chips or tortillas.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients all together and pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together the remaining 4 ingredients and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.

title: peanut butter eggs
directions: Add sugar to a large bowl, add the peanut butter and mix with your hands until well blended.
As mixture gets stiff add the milk a little at a time.
Keep mixing until you feel the mixture sticking together.
Form into eggs.
Melt chocolate in a double boiler.
It is best to refrigerate eggs an hour or two before dipping into the chocolate.

title: crab bake imperial
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Blend in flour, salt, pepper, parsley and chives.
Slowly stir in milk and cook until sauce thickens.
Add lemon peel and juice.
Fold in mushrooms and crab meat.
Spoon into individual scallop shells or casserole dish. Sprinkle top with 1/2 cup grated Cheddar cheese and 1/2 cup buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: holiday jambalaya
directions: In large skillet, saut rice and garlic in butter until rice is golden.
Stir in celery and onion.
Continue sauting until tender, stirring constantly.
Stir in water and next 5 ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Cover.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Add ham, shrimp and tomatoes.
Cover.
Simmer an additional 10 minutes or until rice is tender.
Stir well before serving.
Makes 6 servings (about 6 1/2 cups).

title: sausage and cheese balls
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Blend well.
Roll into balls-size of quarters.
Place on shallow baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: quick coffee cake
directions: Mix and sift dry ingredients.
Work in butter.
Add egg and milk.
Pat into buttered pan.
Mix cinnamon and 3 teaspoons sugar. Sprinkle on top.
Bake in moderately hot oven (375°) about 20 minutes.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Arrange in greased 9 x 12-inch casserole.
Place chicken slices on broccoli.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour over chicken. Sprinkle with vermouth.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: barbecue hot dogs
directions: Bring this to a boil, then pour over hot dogs that have been split down through the center and again about 3 times on each side.
Let simmer in electric skillet as long as you like or bake in 350° oven for about an hour.

title: aunt erlean's chicken pie
directions: Use 1/2 stick of butter to cover the bottom of both shells. Put chicken in bottom of each crust; add soup (diluted) with water and condensed milk.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cover the top of each pie with another shell for top crust.
Cook at 400° until golden brown.
Melt butter over top when done.

title: jello cake
directions: Mix according to package directions.
Bake in tube or Bundt pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: original sausage and egg casserole
directions: Beat eggs and add to other ingredients.
Place in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
(Best if chilled 24 hours before baking.
If only overnight it doesn't get as fluffy.)

title: mom's deer steak
directions: Roll
steak
in
flour and brown on both sides in bacon drippings
in skillet.
Cover steak with water and add remaining ingredients.
Cook until meat is tender.
More liquid can be added.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Remove boiled chicken from bones; cool.
Put back in stock. Bring to boil.
Cook together until noodles are done.
Beat eggs until fluffy, combine with milk and cheese to hot chicken and noodle mixture.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Saute bread cubes in margarine.
Add to casserole leaving some bread cubes for top.
Pour into casserole dish sprayed with Pam.
Bake until brown or firm, about 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: chocolate chews
directions: In a 13 x 9 pan, melt margarine. Sprinkle cookie crumbs on margarine. Press crumbs into pan. Add milk. Pour in coconut and nuts. Press chips into pan. Bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: guacamole
directions: Mash or chop avocados, sprinkle with lemon juice and mix in all the other ingredients.
This can be served immediately, but can be covered with plastic wrap and chill in the refrigerator for 30 minutes or so, to gather flavor and mellow.
Serves 4.

title: delicious corn pudding
directions: Saute onions and pepper in butter for 5 minutes.
Add flour and seasonings.
Stir in milk, egg yolks, corn and bread cubes.
Pour into a buttered Pyrex loaf dish.
Sprinkle crumbs on top, and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: cheese straws
directions: Mix cheese, flour and butter; stir thoroughly.
Add eggs; roll as for pastry.
Cut into 1/2 to 3-inch strips.
Bake at 375° until brown.
Yield:
8 dozen.

title: hot creamy crab dip
directions: In a saucepan, over low heat, heat the olive oil.
Using a fork or a wire whisk, stir in the flour and cook until it bubbles, about 1 minute.
Stir in the evaporated skim milk and stir until the mixture comes to a boil.
Add the fat-free cream cheese, lemon juice, wine, onion powder, Worcestershire sauce, paprika, dill, mustard and pepper, stirring until the cheese melts.
Taste for seasoning, adding a little lemon juice, if desired.
Add the pimentos and crab meat.
Pour mixture into a microwave-safe or ovenproof serving dish.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes or put into a 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Serve with cubes of sourdough bread or vegetable sticks.

title: white candy party mix
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Prepare almond bark according to package directions.
Pour almond bark over ingredients and mix well.
Spread into a thin layer onto the wax paper.
After completely dry, break mixture up and store in bowl.

title: crustless cheese cake
directions: Mix first five ingredients and pour into buttered 9-inch glass pie pan.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.
Remove and cool 15 minutes. The cake will collapse slightly in the center forming a small "well".
Pour the sour cream mixture into the "well" in the cake. Return to oven for 5 minutes to set the sour cream mixture.
Cool and add cherry pie filling to top.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Marinate the first 6 ingredients overnight.
Cook the spaghetti and drain. Add to the marinated ingredients along with the Italian dressing.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together; add pecans last.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or until knife comes out clean.

title: midwest chowder
directions: Bring to a boil 2 cups salted water; add the vegetables and simmer for 10 minutes.
Make a cream sauce of margarine, flour and milk.
Add cheese to sauce.
Add the 2 cups of creamed corn and vegetables including the broth.
Heat but do not boil.

title: old fashioned biscuits
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and sugar in mixing bowl.
Cut in butter or shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
With fork, stir in buttermilk to make a soft dough. Turn out onto lightly floured board; knead 10 times to form smooth ball.
Roll to 6 x 6-inch square.
Put on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
With knife, cut into 12 pieces.
Do not separate.

title: creole peas
directions: Fry bacon.
Remove drippings.
Saute pepper, onions and celery in
drippings.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt, optional. Add peas, drained.
Mix
well.
Add
the
mushroom and tomato soup.
Let simmer.
Pour
into a casserole dish.
Crumble the bacon on
top. Cook
in
a 300° oven until bubbly throughout. Can be prepared ahead of time;
frozen and baked when ready to serve.

title: "classic" carrot cake
directions: Mix together all dry ingredients. Beat together eggs, oil and sugar. Add to dry ingredients. Mix in 2 cups cooked mashed carrots; add nuts and raisins. Bake at 350° for 1 hour in greased and floured large tube pan.

title: pink lady salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Stir well and it's ready to eat.

title: quick pecan pies(two)
directions: Beat eggs.
Mix according to listing.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Makes two thin pies.

title: punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in warm water.
Add rest of juices and water. To every 3 quarts of this mixture, add 1 bottle ginger ale.
Yields 141 (5 ounce) cups.

title: quick tacos
directions: Cook and stir ground beef and onion in 10-inch skillet until beef is brown; drain.
Stir in seasoning mix (dry) and water. Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Spoon beef mixture onto chips.
Top with remaining ingredients.

title: baked apples
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Sprinkle inside apple cavities. Combine last 6 ingredients and stir until blended.
Place on top of apples as "streusel" topping.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes or until done in 350° oven.

title: shrimply divine
directions: Blend in order given.
Chill one hour longer.
Makes 1 2/3 cups of dip.

title: kathleen's salad
directions: Cut up broccoli into small bite size pieces.
Add finely chopped onion.
Stir in sunflower seeds and raisins.

title: zucchini applesauce(good with pork or lamb)
directions: In a large saucepan; bring to a boil zucchini, apple, water, sugar, cloves and salt.
Reduce heat, cover and then cook 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove cover; continue cooking until all liquid has evaporated.
Discard cloves.
Mash mixture or blend in partially covered blender container until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice and cinnamon.
Cover and refrigerate.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: chicken kabobs
directions: Bring to
a
boil
and simmer for 5 minutes.
When cool add chicken cut up in chunks and marinate for at least 2 hours before cooking.
Better
if
overnight.
After the chicken is ready put your
meat,
fruit	and vegetables on the stick and grill.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Saute
onions until transparent.
Set aside and fry sausage until done. Remove and place in strainer to remove all grease.
Mix onion and sausage together and put in pie crust.
Grate cheese and put over sausage mixture.
Mix milk, eggs, half and half, salt, pepper and parsley.
Pour over top. Bake at 375° for 35 minutes, then at 350° for 15 minutes.
Let set for 15 minutes before serving.

title: fruit salad and pudding mix
directions: Drain all fruit, reserving 2 cups of mixed juices.
Layer drained fruit, strawberries, cherries and bananas into bowl. Combine pudding mix with juices in bowl, beating until thick.
Pour over fruit.
Do not toss.
Chill for 2 hours before serving. Yields 15 servings.

title: winter stew delight
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Combine all ingredients in a large, oven proof stew pot. Cover and bake 11/2-2 hours until tender, stirring occasionally. If necessary, add more broth or tomato juice. Serve with homemade bread or biscuits.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°.
Generously butter a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Mix the flour, salt, paprika, mustard and cayenne pepper together; set aside.
Melt the butter in a skillet, add green pepper and onion; cook until soft.
Stir in the flour mixture and cook, stirring and smoothing, for 2 or 3 minutes.
Add milk, stirring constantly, bring it to the boiling point.
Stir in the corn and egg yolk.
Spoon into the baking dish and sprinkle with the crumbs.
Bake for 25 minutes until the crumbs are brown.

title: quick carrots
directions: Cook carrots in a waterless pan, or with 2 tablespoons water in a heavy, nonstick frypan with a tight-fitting lid.
After carrots come to a boil, turn heat down and simmer until tender (about 5 minutes).
Stir in orange concentrate.
Decorate with thin orange slices.
Lightly toasted, slivered almonds also make a tasty garnish.
Serves 6.

title: goofy cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients into pan (8 or 9-inch square).
Make 3 holes.
Put cooking oil in first hole, vinegar in 2nd hole and vanilla in third.
Pour water over all.
Stir with fork until blended.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes in 350° oven.
Frost when cool.

title: fat free chocolate cake
directions: Spray Bundt pan with light Pam spray.
Mix the first 6 ingredients together and set aside.
Stir next 2 ingredients with wire whisk for 1 minute, then mix egg whites and corn syrup. Gradually stir
liquid ingredients to dry.
Mix with wire whisk until smooth.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 16, 140 calories and 0 grams fat per serving.

title: banana split cake
directions: Bake cake according to package directions in jelly roll pan. Let cool.
Mix pudding with milk and cream cheese.
Spread on cooled cake.
Spread drained pineapple over pudding mixture.
Top with bananas.
Spread with Cool Whip.
Garnish with nuts and cherries.

title: pork with bay leaves
directions: Heat the oil in a saucepan just large enough to hold the meat. Add pork and brown
over moderate heat for about 10 minutes.
Add juniper berries, cloves, bay leaves, onions, salt and pepper. Lower the heat and cook the meat until very tender, about 1 1/2 hours, adding 1/2 cup wine, a little at a time.

title: slaw
directions: Boil sugar, vinegar and turmeric.
Pour over cabbage mixture. This slaw will keep for weeks in refrigerator.

title: georgia's butter icing
directions: Combine margarine, Crisco, vanilla, salt and sugar; beat at high speed, adding hot milk gradually until all sugar is melted. Keep milk hot while melting down sugar.
Refrigerate when done or frost cake immediately.
Refrigerate cake.

title: drunken chicken
directions: Place chicken in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Mix the cream of chicken and cream of mushroom soups together and add the white wine.
Mix well.
Pour over chicken.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Place chicken on deep platter or casserole dish and pour the gravy over chicken.
Good served with rice.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or celery soup

title: honey and spice chicken
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Brush chicken with margarine.
Place on a rack in a shallow pan.
Bake 40 minutes.
Mix Heinz sauce and honey; brush both sides of chicken.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until tender.
Brush again with remaining mix and serve.

title: fruit sauce for ham
directions: Heat syrup and water.
Blend cornstarch, mustard and vinegar. Stir slowly into syrup.
Cook and stir until clear and thickened. Add fruit cocktail and heat thoroughly.
Serve hot over ham. Makes 2 cups.

title: coconut cream layer pie
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, sugar, topping mix, milk and 2 teaspoons vanilla until light and fluffy.
Pour into pie shells.
Spread 1 cup coconut on each pie and chill several hours.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Boil chicken and cool cut in small pieces.
Cook spaghetti and drain well.
Mix sour cream, tomatoes and cream of mushroom soup. Set aside.
Mix everything together and heat until hot.
Oven 350°

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve the jello with the boiling water and add cold water; chill.
Mix remaining ingredients and fold into chilled jello. Chill until set.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Sift the first 3 ingredients together and add fruit cocktail. Mix well and pour into well-greased pan.
Sprinkle top of layers with brown sugar and 1/2 cup of chopped pecans.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: baked ziti
directions: Cook ground beef and Italian sauce in frypan until done; drain.
Set aside.
Mix Ricotta, eggs, garlic powder, basil, salt and pepper together; set aside (in refrigerator).
Boil (pasta) ziti according to directions for al dente or not well done (still a little firm).
Add 1 cup sauce.
Get a pan and put enough sauce to cover bottom; layer pasta, beef and sausage, Mozzarella, Italian cheese and sauce.
Continue to top of pan.
Top pasta with Mozzarella.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes to 1 hour. This can be frozen before cooking, then thawed and cooked.

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil butter, syrup and brown sugar together for 5 minutes. Remove from heat and add soda and vanilla.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Take out of oven and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake until cheese is bubbly.

title: people pleasin' pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream sugar and margarine. Add egg, pumpkin and milk. Mix together the spices and flour. Add to creamed mixture. Drop into ungreased cookie sheet by spoonful. Bake 12-15 minutes at 375°. Let cool. Drip frosting over cookies. Makes 6 dozen.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet; draining excess grease.
Add taco seasoning and water; bring to a boil.
Simmer about 15 minutes and add Ranch Style beans and chopped onion; stirring occasionally.
Pour meat mixture over corn chips in the bottom of a medium-sized bowl.
Add chopped lettuce, tomatoes and grated cheese.

title: company beans
directions: Heat cooking oil in large skillet.
Add ground beef and onion. Cook until meat is well browned.
Drain oil from meat.
Add remaining ingredients to meat mixture.
Place in greased 2-quart casserole dish and bake at 350°
for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: *holy bread
directions: Dissolve yeast according to package directions.
Add to flour. Add salt and rest of water.
Knead about 7 minutes.
Let rest 15 minutes, covered.
Cut dough in 2 equal parts.
Pat into round shape.
Place in round 8-inch cake pan that has been sprinkle with flour.
Prick with toothpick.
Let rise 3/4 to 1 hour or until doubled in size.
Should be in warm place.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: turkey salad
directions: In medium bowl, stir together mayonnaise, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Add turkey, celery, carrots and onion; toss to coat well.
Cover and chill at least 2 hours.
Makes 5 cups.

title: microwave frosted cauliflower
directions: Remove woody base from cauliflower.
Wash and wrap in waxed paper.
Cook 6 minutes per pound.
Mix together mayonnaise, mustard and onion.
Spread over cauliflower.
Sprinkle cheese over top. Return to microwave and melt cheese, 1 to 1 1/2 minutes.

title: chili dip
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Mix with chili (no beans).
Cover bottom of pan with sour cream.
Cover sour cream with hamburger mixture.
Cover with Velveeta cheese and put in oven until melted.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add salt and onion.
Sprinkle with the flour.
Add other spices and stir in catsup.
Then simmer until thick as desired.

title: chocoloca
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in large saucepan.
Add egg and cold water; mix.
Add hot water.
Heat on high until mixture is thick. Add vanilla.

title: strawberry hard sauce
directions: Sift sugar.
Beat until soft the butter.
Add the sugar gradually.
Beat these ingredients until they are well blended. Beat in strawberries.
Chill the sauce.
This makes a good sauce, but it is better with the addition of cream and egg white.
Makes about 1 2/3 cupfuls.

title: shrimp and grits casserole
directions: Cook grits in water and salt.
Add remaining ingredients to hot grits.
Mix until cheese is melted.
Bake at 350° in 13 x 9-inch pan 20 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: rosemarino salad
directions: Cook pasta, drain and let cool.
Drain pineapple and oranges, saving juices.
In saucepan, combine flour, sugar, eggs and salt with reserved juiced.
Bring to boil and thicken.
Pour over pasta and refrigerate overnight.
Upon serving, fold in pineapple, oranges, drained cherries, coconut and Cool Whip.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together well to form a ball.
Place in loaf pan.
Bake at 325° until done (45 minutes to 1 hour).

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done. Remove bones. Cook rice in chicken broth until tender. Mix all ingredients. Place in casserole dish. Fills a 3-quart dish full. Bake for 45 minutes at 325°.

title: roasted turkey
directions: When defrosted, wash off the turkey and clean thoroughly. Butter the entire bird. Place the following spices in the cavity of the bird-- rosemary, oregano, thyme, salt. and pepper to taste. Place the turkey in a roasting pan on a bed of carrots, celery, and purple onions. You can stuff the cavity of the turkey with a prepared dressing of your choice if desired. Bake at 425 degrees for 30 minutes. Bake at 325 degrees for remainder of time specified on the turkey. Baste every 30 minutes.

title: peach julep
directions: If using canned peaches, drain and puree them in saucepan. If fresh peaches, peel, puree and add sugar to them in saucepan. Add 3 mint sprigs and stir until mint is thoroughly bruised. Cool.
Remove mint and add the juices and grated bits of rind; chill.
Just before serving, add ginger ale and garnish with remaining mint sprigs.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix well, then fold in one cup semi-sweet chocolate chips. Pour in greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: decorator buttercream frosting
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients on high for 4 minutes, until like whipped butter. Then add Sweetex and mix again on high for 3 minutes, until glossy. Don't overbeat or it becomes airy and separates. Use pastry tube with decorator tips to frost cake. Can store in the refrigerator up to 6 months.

title: apple jelly
directions: Measure apple juice and lemon juice into 6-quart pan.
Add pectin to fruit juice.
Stir thoroughly to dissolve and scrape sides of pan to make sure all pectin dissolves.
Bring to a boil, stirring to prevent scorching.
Add sugar and mix well.
Continue stirring and bring to full rolling boil.
Remove jelly from heat and pour into containers.
Seal with USDA Boil Water Bath or paraffin.
Makes about 4 (8 ounce) jars.

title: crumbly pie crust
directions: Sift or mix together flour and sugar.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Put on top of filling and bake.

title: minty melon bowl
directions: Mix all ingredients, except jelly, in a salad bowl.
Stir jelly with a fork until soft.
Pour over fruit and toss lightly. Cover and chill.
Garnish with mint leaves, if desired.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix until well blended.
Cook slowly; keep temperature low, no boiling, stewing or steaming.
Season to taste with the spice of life.

title: ranch style round steak
directions: Combine catsup with brown sugar, onion, salt, pepper, ginger and cloves in a small saucepan.
Add wine vinegar and oil; cook slowly for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cool.
Place steak and marinade in plastic bag (carefully pressing out air).

Tie securely and place in pan in fridge for 6 hours or overnight. Remove steak from marinade (reserving marinade) and place on grill. Broil at moderate temperature for 25 to 40 minutes, brushing on marinade and turning occasionally.
Carve in thin slices, diagonally, across the grain of the meat.
Serve.

title: beef n biscuit casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown beef, onions and pepper.
Add tomato sauce and seasonings; simmer.
Separate the 10 biscuits into 20 pieces.
Press 10 into bottom of an 8-inch square pan.
Combine sour cream, egg and 1/2 of cheese.
Stir into meat mixture and spoon onto dough.
Arrange remaining biscuits on top and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: herbal salves
directions: Put herbal oil in water.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Strain through a cheesecloth or muslin into another pan and repeat these steps until there are only 2 ounces left.
Add olive oil and simmer until all the water has evaporated.
Add tincture of benzoin and bees wax.

title: no-bake pineapple marmalade squares
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, 2 tablespoons sugar and margarine in 8-ounce square baking dish; pat mixture firmly and evenly onto bottom of dish. Freeze 10 minutes.
Beat sour cream, cream cheese, remaining 1/2 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon marmalade in medium bowl until smooth and blended; set aside.

title: brown sugar seafoam
directions: Boil sugar and water until mixture forms a firm but not brittle ball when tested in cold water.
Beat egg whites stiff. Pour sugar syrup over egg whites and beat until mixture stands in peaks.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls of mixture onto waxed paper.
Cool.

title: strawberries crush ice
directions: Defrost packs 2 hours early before starting recipe.
Pour ingredients in order to list in a blender and push "whip" for 33 seconds, then add ice cubes. "Crush" for 45 seconds.
Freeze for 15 minutes.

title: banana-bran muffins
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Set aside.
Measure cereal, milk and mashed bananas into mixing bowl. Stir to combine.
Let stand 1 to 2 minutes until cereal is softened.
Add egg and oil.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients to cereal mixture, stirring only until combined.
Pour batter evenly into 12 greased 2 1/2-inch (or 6 jumbo size) muffin pan cups. Bake in oven at 400° about 25 minutes or until muffins are golden brown.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix well and chill overnight.

title: oklahoma baby back ribs
directions: Place ribs, meat side up, in roasting pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 2 hours; drain.
Combine remaining ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat; simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes.
Cool at room temperature for 1 hour.
Brush sauce over ribs.
Reduce oven to 300° and bake, uncovered, basting occasionally, for 1 to 1 1/2 hours longer.

title: butter pecan torte
directions: Crush crackers and mix with melted butter.
Use 2/3 in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Save 1/3 for topping.

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, milk and sugar in large bowl with wire whisk until smooth.
Gently stir in whipped topping.
Spread on bottom of crust.
Pour 1 cup milk into bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Beat with wire whisk until well blended, 1 to 2 minutes (mixture will be thick).

title: spinach dip
directions: Place spinach on paper towels and squeeze until barely moist; set aside.
Position knife blade in food processor bowl.
Add next 5 ingredients; process until smooth.
Add spinach and bell pepper; process until pepper is finely minced.
Spoon into a bowl, cover and chill.
Serve with plain crackers or carrot sticks.
Yields 2 cups (about 16 calories per tablespoon).

title: chili
directions: Brown ground chuck and onions.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Simmer about 2 hours.
Add kidney beans for the last 30 minutes of cooking time.

title: cherry tortillas
directions: Fill tortilla with cherry pie filling and roll up.
Add remaining ingredients and place in a cake pan.
Lay tortillas over the mixture.
Bake at 350 degrees for one hour, or until most of the juice is gone from the pan.

title: zesty baked potatoes
directions: Scrub and rinse potatoes.
Cut potatoes into thin slices, but do not cut all the way through.
Use a handle of a spoon to prevent knife from cutting all the way.
Put potatoes in a baking dish, then fan slightly.
Sprinkle with salt and drizzle with butter. Sprinkle with herbs.

title: apricot chicken
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together.
Place chicken in a pan. Pour the sauce over the chicken.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°. Change to 350°
last half hour if you feel chicken is not cooking fast enough.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Cut chickens in serving pieces and brown in hot oil.
Remove chicken from pan.
Add onions, peppers and garlic.
Cook until slightly browned. Return chicken to pan. Add remaining ingredients and simmer 1/2 hour or until chicken is tender. Serve with noodles. Serves 6.

title: frozen dessert
directions: Cream together cream cheese and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients and put together and then freeze.

title: carrot souffle
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender and blend well at high speed.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Makes 6 servings.

title: mexican salad
directions: Spread on a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.

title: buttermilk biscuit mix
directions: Mix all ingredients, except buttermilk.
This makes a large amount and may be stored in an airtight container until ready to use.
When ready to use, add enough buttermilk for amount of mix used.

title: nannie's japanese fruit cake
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients well. Put in 2 round layer pans, reserving enough batter for a third pan.
Add to this batter the cinnamon, ground cloves and allspice, along with raisins. Stir this well. Put into third pan.
Bake all 3 pans at 350° until done, 30 minutes or until wooden pick tests done/clean.

title: dilly casserole bread
directions: Soften yeast in water.
Heat cottage cheese to lukewarm.
Mix all ingredients, beat well.
Add enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until double (about 1 hour).
Stir down and turn into well-greased 8-inch round casserole.
Let rise in warm place for about 30 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; add pie filling and pineapple.
Chill until firm.
Mix cream cheese, 1 cup nuts, sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread on top.

title: easy chili
directions: Brown ground beef and onions, then drain.
In a 3-quart pan, mix together everything and simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pineapple cheese muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Line muffin pan with baking cups. Mix pineapple with juice and remaining ingredients. Beat 30 seconds. Fill muffin cups 3/4 full. Bake until light brown, about 15 minutes. Yield: 12 muffins.

title: bread
directions: Heat 1 1/2 quarts water to lukewarm; crumble yeast into it. Add sugar, shortening and potato that has been cooked and mashed in its own water.
Stir in flour which salt has been added to. Makes 6 to 8 small loaves.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: delicious chocolate icing
directions: Place bowl in dish of ice and beat ingredients together with beater until stiff and creamy.

title: cordon bleu turkey rolls
directions: Marinate turkey in dressing 4 to 6 hours.
Gently pound flat. Place 1/2 slice ham and 1/2 slice cheese in center.
Roll cutlet so cheese and ham are contained. Wrap with 1 slice bacon.
Hold in place with wooden picks. Bake for 20 minutes at 350°, then broil until bacon is crisp.

title: brown rice
directions: Wash rice.
Add consomme, bouillon cubes (dissolved in 1 can hot water), salt to taste, onion and margarine.
Put in casserole dish with lid on it.
Bake in oven for 1 hour at 350°.

title: crock-pot dressing
directions: Cook celery and onion in butter until tender; stir in bread cubes and corn bread.
Add all seasonings and eggs.
Add soup and broth; mix thoroughly.
More broth may be added if needed.
Spoon lightly into 6 or 8-quart crock-pot.
Cook on low for 4 to 6 hours.

title: chocolate chip macaroon angel food
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Stir together powdered sugar and flour.
In a large bowl beat egg whites and cream of tartar.
Beating at high speed, gradually add 1 cup sugar, 2 tablespoons at a time.
Add salt, almond and vanilla until stiff.

title: baked donuts
directions: Beat together Margarine, Egg and Sugar.
Set aside.
Mix together Flour, Baking Powder, Salt and Nutmeg.
Mix two sets of ingredients alternating with Milk.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 350 for 20 - 30 minutes.
Roll in a mixture of sugar and cinnamon while still warm.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: 7 minute frosting
directions: Combine egg whites, sugar, tartar and water in top of double boiler.
Beat on high speed 1 minute.
Place over boiling water and beat on high for 7 minutes.
Remove from pan of water.
Add vanilla.
Beat 2 minutes longer on high.
Frosts two (9-inch) layers.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Pour juice off the pineapple.
Add enough water to make 1 cup; bring to a boil.
Pour over jello.
Mix well. Add cheese (room temperature).
Add ice cream and pineapple.
Refrigerate.
Ready in 15 minutes.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: On low speed, cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, and mix until blended.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with milk, then stir in the blueberries.

title: dynamite cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small bowl, combine crust ingredients with fork and press firmly over bottom and partway up sides of 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix mushroom, celery and chicken soups with rice and water in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Place chicken on top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: peanut surprise brownies
directions: Mix brownies according to directions on box.
Pour brownie mix into paper cupcake holders 3/4 full.
Place one Reese's peanut butter cup into the center (remove paper from cup) of
brownie dough.
Bake according to directions on box.

title: cheesy chicken casserole
directions: Cook pepper, onion and butter in microwave for 2 to 3 minutes. Mix all together and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with Velveeta cheese and cover.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: shrimp italianne kabobs
directions: Wash shrimp.
Remove shells.
Devein.
Mix together next 6 ingredients.
Add shrimp.
Cover in refrigerator for 1 to 2 hours. Thread shrimp on skewers.
Cook over hot coals 15 minutes.

title: oreo cookies and ice cream
directions: Pat melted margarine and cookies in the bottom of an 11 x 14-inch cake pan.
Spread softened ice cream on top and put in freezer.
Melt sugar, chocolate and margarine together.
Gradually add 2/3 cup evaporated milk (small can) and stir until thickened. Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Cool.
When cool, spread over ice cream. Freeze.
When chocolate layer is frozen, add a layer of Cool Whip and freeze.

title: blueberry jello salad
directions: Mix jello and boiling water.
Add blueberries and crushed pineapple.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan and chill.
Beat together sour cream, cream cheese and sugar.
Spread over jello.
Spread crushed walnuts on top.

title: oven easy chicken
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a paper bag.
Shake pieces of chicken to coat well.
Melt margarine in a baking dish.
Arrange chicken pieces, skin side down, in dish.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Turn pieces over after 30 minutes of baking.

title: mary lee's spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute onion in oil.
Just before light brown, add minced garlic.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
If too thick, add water to proper consistency.

title: taco dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Crumble and brown ground beef in skillet. Drain off drippings. Spread beans in ungreased 2 1/2-quart shallow baking dish, then top with ground beef.
Pour salsa over ground beef; sprinkle olives and onions over top. Bake 20 to 30 minutes or until heated through.
Spread with sour cream while hot and serve with chips.

title: ranch-style lentil casserole
directions: Brown beef.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Place in baking dish.
Bake at 400°
for 30 minutes.

title: chile rellenos egg rolls
directions: Slit each chile lengthwise and rinse under cold water to remove seeds.
Remove stems and set aside.
Cook beef, onion and garlic in a skillet until meat is browned.
Add cheese and seasonings, stirring well.
Place 2 tablespoons beef mixture on each chile, roll up jellyroll fashion.
Place chiles diagonally (off center) of each egg roll wrapper.
Fold corner over chile, fold sides over and brush edges of wrapper lightly with water. Roll up and press edges to seal.
Heat vegetable oil to depth of 4 to 5 inches to 375°.
Fry 2 to 3 at a time until golden brown.

title: pork and sauerkraut
directions: Combine all and cook in slow oven for 2 hours at 300°.

title: sweet potato home fries
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Peel sweet potatoes and cut each into eights. Put in a bowl and add olive oil and other spices. Stir well to coat evenly. Spread in a single layer in a large baking pan. Bake 15 minutes or until tender. Remove potatoes from oven and turn heat to broil. Put on top rack and broil a few minutes to brown edges. Serve with salsa ketchup.

title: easy homemade strawberry ice cream
directions: In ice cream freezer container, combine all ingredients and mix well.
Freeze according to manufacturer's instructions.

title: freezer strawberry jam
directions: Cut off tender corn.
Put in pot like you are going to cook; cover with 2/3 water.
Bring to boil.
Let boil 2 or 3 minutes. Stir so it won't stick.
Pour in colander and drain.
Put on cookie sheet and cool; ready to freeze.

title: cary's famous pancake
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In mixing bowl, combine flour, milk, eggs and nutmeg.
Beat lightly.
Leave batter a little lumpy.
Melt butter in pie pan in oven; do not burn.
Pour in batter and bake 15 to 20 minutes, until golden brown.
Sprinkle with sugar and return briefly to oven.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with lemon juice. Serve with additional confectioners sugar and lemon available at the table.
Serves 2.

title: cheddar cheese and asparagus soup
directions: Melt butter in heavy, medium size saucepan over medium heat. Add asparagus and garlic.
Saute about 5 minutes.
Gradually blend in flour. Cook, stirring, 3 to 5 minutes.
Reduce heat to medium-low.
Gradually stir in 1 cup milk and cheese. Cook, stirring, 5 minutes or until cheese is melted and smooth.
Stir in remaining milk, mustard, salt and pepper. Gently heat, stirring, until soup is hot.
To serve, remove garlic. Garnish with shredded cheese, if you wish.
May substitute asparagus with tiny broccoli flowerets.
For extra color, add 1/2 cup sauteed diced sweet red pepper.

title: broccoli
directions: Prepare squash by cutting into serving pieces; remove any seeds and fibers.
Place squash in ungreased 13 1/2 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Season cut edges with salt and pepper.
Dot with butter.
Pour water into dish to 1/4 depth.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake for 1 hour at 375° or until tender.

title: cream cheese party cupcakes
directions: Beat cream cheese in a large mixing bowl until soft and creamy.
Gradually add 1 cup sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating after each addition.
Stir in 1 1/2 teaspoons vanilla, stirring well.
Spoon batter into paper lined miniature muffin pans filling 2/3 full.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Combine sour cream, 1/4 cup sugar and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla, stirring well.
Spoon 1/4 teaspoon sour cream on each cupcake; top with small amount of strawberry preserves in center of sour cream mixture.
Return cupcakes to oven; continue baking 5 minutes.
Regular cupcake pans may be used, but time should be adjusted.

title: dried beef dip
directions: Combine half of beef with other ingredients; roll in ball, then roll in rest of beef.
Makes a great party dip.

title: fumi salad
directions: Brown almonds and sesame seeds in oil. Crush noodles in packages (seasoning mix won't be used). Combine all ingredients.

title: famous wesson fruitcake(a recipe treasured by homemakers for over fifty years)
directions: Heat oven to 275°.
Line 2 (9 x 5 x 3-inch) pans with lightly greased brown paper.
Combine Wesson, sugar and eggs; beat 2 minutes.
In large bowl, combine 1 cup flour with fruits and nuts. Sift remaining flour with baking powder, salt and spices.
Stir into Wesson mixture alternately with orange juice.
Pour batter over fruit mixture; blend well.
Turn into prepared pans.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Melt butter in pan; add and stir in flour, salt and pepper. Stir until smooth over low heat until thick (10 minutes).
Remove from heat and stir in 3 cups cheese until melted.
Put mixture over macaroni and pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Spread remaining cheese on top of casserole before placing in oven.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin spice cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Add dates.
Mix well.
Bake in layer tins at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Frost with peanut butter icing.

title: barbecue potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients together except potatoes.
Wash potatoes and quarter lengthwise.
Then halve the quarters lengthwise to make thick strips.
Arrange on cookie sheet and spread potatoes with mixture and bake for 45 minutes.

title: shrimp remoulade sauce
directions: Add and mix all ingredients except shrimp, lettuce and celery; mix with enough boiled shrimp to cover them well.
Serve over a bed of shredded lettuce and finely sliced celery.
Serve with crackers and butter.

title: divinity candy
directions: Place in saucepan over low heat sugar, corn syrup and water. Stir only to mix the ingredients, then cook without stirring to 255°.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
When temperature of 255° is reached, remove from heat and pour, beating constantly with electric mixer, in a fine stream into the stiffly beaten egg whites.
Continue beating until mixture holds its shape and loses its gloss.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Spread in buttered 9 x 12-inch pan or drop quickly by teaspoon onto waxed paper.

title: pie crust
directions: Melt margarine.
Put flour and salt in pie plate.
Pour melted margarine in.
Mix with tablespoon until moist.
Take spoon, spread over pie plate.
Bake at 350° until light brown.
May fix ahead of time.

title: chili con carne
directions: Crumble and brown ground beef.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer for 1 hour.
Makes 4 servings.
For 6 servings, use 2 cans kidney beans.
May be served over white rice.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions.
Drain thoroughly.
Mix together remaining ingredients.
Add to spinach. Mix together well.
Pour into shallow baking dish.
Top with a little extra Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until casserole is bubbly.
Serves 8.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Prepare marinade basting sauce.
Place chicken in a bowl. Pour marinade over.
Remove from marinade.
Use it as a basting sauce for chicken.
Place chicken on preheated barbecue grill or broiler.
Baste with sauce on all sides.
Grill chicken, basting and turning every 10 minutes, for about 30 minutes or until chicken is done and juices run clear when pierced with a fork.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix all ingredients but the boiling water.
Add boiling water slowly.
Let rise until double.
Knead well on well floured board. Roll thin; cut in small rectangular strips.
Dip in melted butter. Arrange in layers in greased jello ring mold until mold is half full.
Let rise again.
Bake at 350° until well browned.
Makes 4 ring molds.

title: almost homemade soup
directions: Combine broth and dry soup in a large kettle.
(I also add about 2 cups of water).
Bring to boil.
Add frozen vegetables and cook for five minutes on medium heat.
Return to boil and add soup macaroni; lower heat and cook until macaroni is done, about 7 minutes.

title: grandmother's lemon pie
directions: Add cream of tartar to egg whites and beat until frothy; gradually add sugar while beating the egg whites until the mixture will form peaks. Add to pie. (Be sure to seal the meringue around the pie crust.) Brown in a 400° oven just long enough to brown the mixture.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add sour cream and vanilla.
Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Add two eggs and one cup of flour mixture to creamed mixture; blend well. Alternate adding two eggs and one cup of flour mixture (ending with flour), mixing well after each addition.

title: preacher's casserole
directions: Fry celery, hamburger and onions until onions and celery are transparent.
Add water, chow mein noodles, chili powder and soups.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart dish and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: southern okra
directions: Mix all ingredients together except okra and cook until tender.
Add okra and simmer until done.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Brown bacon. Add onion and green pepper. Do not drain.
Pour on cooked macaroni.
Add grated cheese, salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
(Cover if it starts to brown.)

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken until tender and debone.
Cut into pieces.
Save broth.
Mix can of Veg-All with chicken pieces.
Add can of soup. Add 3/4 soup can of broth.
Put all this into 9 x 13-inch baking dish, sprayed with Pam. Mix Bisquick with milk.
Pour over vegetable and meat mixture.
Melt margarine and pour over top of Bisquick.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until crust is brown.

title: lazy man cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in 13 x 9-inch dish.
Mix sugar, flour and milk.
Pour into center of dish.
Do not stir.
Place peaches over top.
Drizzle peach juice over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: firey cajun shrimp
directions: Mix all ingredients except lemon slices and shrimp, over low heat.
Pour sauce to cover bottom of two 9 x 13-inch baking dishes (or slightly smaller for one).
Place shrimp[ and lemon slices on top.
Cover with remaining sauce.
Bake, uncovered, for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°, stirring once or twice.
Shrimp should turn pink, but do not overcook.
Serve with French bread to dip into sauce. Or over pasta.

title: raisin patties
directions: Boil raisins a few minutes; drain, dry and cool.
Add sugar to eggs (well beaten).
Add vanilla.
Mix all together; stir in melted butter the size of an egg.
Make pie dough.
Pour mixture in
and bake in muffin tins at 400° for 10 minutes; reduce heat to 350° and continue to bake for about 20 minutes.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each.

title: sauerkraut relish
directions: In a bowl, combine sugar, salad oil and vinegar; stir thoroughly and set aside.
In a pot, combine onions, celery, peppers and drained (not rinsed) sauerkraut.
Bring to a boil, mixing thoroughly for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Pour oil/vinegar mixture over it and mix thoroughly.
Cover and chill for 1 hour before serving.
Makes a good side dish.

title: popsicles
directions: Mix Kool-Aid like the pack said.
Pour into ice trays.
Cover with Saran Wrap.
Poke sticks into each hole.
Freeze overnight.

title: dam good cookies
directions: Cream the first 5 ingredients, then add the remaining ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
This makes a large batch.

title: sugarless cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients and add remaining ingredients to moisten. Drop by teaspoons onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes. Dough will be thin.

title: traditional key lime pie
directions: Place the condensed milk, cream cheese, lime juice and vanilla in a food processor or in a large bowl with an electric beater. Blend or whisk on medium speed for 15 minutes.
Place filling in the cooled, baked crust and refrigerate at least 8 hours before serving.
Garnish with fresh whipped cream and twisted lime slices.

title: upside-down ham loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter or margarine in a loaf pan; add sugar and mix well.
Arrange the pineapple cubes in this mixture.

title: chicken-vegetable stir-fry
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients in small bowl.
Stir in broth, corn syrup and soy sauce.
Mix until blended.
Set aside.
In a skillet or wok, heat 3 tablespoons oil over medium-high heat.
Add broccoli, carrots and onion.
Stir-fry 2 minutes.
Add chestnuts and peas; stir-fry 1 minute.
Remove from skillet.
Heat remaining oil.
Add chicken and stir-fry 2 minutes until chicken turns white.
Return vegetables to skillet.
Add cornstarch mixture. Bring to a boil.
Boil 1 minute.
Serve over rice.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix sugar & cocoa in saucepan.
Add milk.
Cook over medium heat until.
Desired thickness.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream the margarine; add sugar gradually, mixing well.
Break one egg at a time into a small bowl, breaking yellow and mixing slightly, then add to sugar-margarine mixture, beating well after each addition.
Measure the flour into a bowl; stir in baking soda, mixing well.
Add alternately to the sugar-margarine-egg mixture a small portion of the buttermilk mix, then a small portion of the flour.
Mix well after each addition.
Continue adding small portions until all
is mixed.
Pour into Bundt pan; bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cake is done when it begins pulling away from sides of pan.
Take care not to move cake too much until done to keep from falling.

title: escalloped pineapple
directions: Mix eggs and milk; beat well.
Add sugar, melted margarine, pineapple and bread.
Pour in a Pyrex baking dish that has been well-greased with margarine.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Good hot or cold.

title: harvey wallbanger's cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 10-inch Bundt pan. Combine cake mix, eggs, orange juice, oil, Galliano and vodka in large mixing bowl.
Beat at medium speed with electric mixer for 4 minutes.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 25 minutes.
Invert onto serving plate.
Cool completely.
Dust with confectioners sugar.

title: quick-n-easy brownies
directions: Place chocolate and butter in a 2-quart glass bowl.
Microwave on half-power for 2 minutes or until mixture is melted.
Stir 2 to 3 times during melting.
Stir in sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Blend well.
Stir into chocolate mixture.
Stir in nuts.

title: french market soup
directions: *Can substitute any combination to equal 2 cups.

title: peach crumbler
directions: Arrange peaches in buttered glass pie plate; sprinkle in lemon juice.
Blend flour, sugar, butter and salt until the mixture resembles cornmeal; sprinkle over peaches.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes until peaches are soft and top is bubbly and brown. Serve hot or cold with vanilla ice cream.

title: diabetic apricot bread(a sweet loaf filled with bits of dried apricots.)
directions: Beat together the eggs and mashed banana until creamy.
Add water, vanilla extract and oil; beat.
Measure in flour, baking soda and baking powder; beat well.
Stir in chopped apricot until evenly blended.
Spoon batter into an oiled and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Spread batter evenly in pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes, or until a knife inserted comes out clean.
Cool completely on a wire rack before slicing.
Serves 6.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Grease 1 large or 2 small loaf pans.
Pour batter and bake in 325 degree oven for 50 to 55 minutes (less time if using small pans).

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put all ingredients into a flat baking dish, putting the chicken on top.
Cover with lid or foil.
Bake at 350° for one hour or until rice and chicken are done.
Lean pork chops can be substituted for chicken.

title: cinnamon baked apples
directions: Core apples without cutting through bottom skin and peel about 1-inch strip of skin from stem end of each apple.
If necessary, cut bottom of each apple so it will stand upright.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix lemon juice with milk.
Drain pineapple and add Cool Whip and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into crust and chill.
Makes 2 pies.

title: pasta with broccoli sauce
directions: Cut stalk and stems off broccoli.
Steam flowerets until crisp-tender.
Drain.
Heat olive oil in medium saucepan.
Saute garlic until pale golden.
Add chicken broth and butter.
Stir in basil, oregano, salt and pepper.
Cook pasta as directed: drain. Stir in broccoli mixture with cooked pasta.
Place cooked pasta in large bowl.
Add Parmesan cheese and toss well.
Serves 6 as a side dish, 4 as a main dish.

title: lime pie
directions: Combine sugar and water and bring to a full boil.
Remove from heat and add Jell-O.
Stir until dissolved.
Place sugar/water/Jell-O mixture in refrigerator and chill until syrupy. Beat chilled evaporated milk on highest mixer speed until doubled in volume.
Add Jell-O mixture and whip until well blended.
To make the crust, place wafers in the bottom and the sides of a pie plate.
(This recipe will make 2 large or 3 small pies.)
Chill at least 6 to 8 hours before serving.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Cut up chicken into bite size pieces (about 1-inch).
Dip chicken in milk-egg mixture; roll in bread crumbs.
Brown chicken in oil, adding oil each time you add chicken.
Place chicken in roasting pan.
Pour drained pineapple over chicken.
Mix Worcestershire sauce and Saucy Susan; pour over chicken.
Stir. Bake at 250° for 30 minutes.

title: chex mix
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Put cereals, pretzels and nuts into roasting pan.
Melt butter in pan; blend in oil, Worcestershire sauce and garlic salt.
Sprinkle over dry ingredients; mix well. Bake 1 1/2 hours.
Stir several times while baking.

title: peas cantonese
directions: Saute onion and celery in margarine.
Add soup, flour, peas (cooked), salt and pepper.
Pour into casserole dish.
Top with stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: sausage dip
directions: Brown sausage; add softened cream cheese and tomatoes.
Heat. Serve warm in small crock-pot.
Use scoopers for dipping.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash and remove stems.
Dice stems very fine.
Chop onion very fine; use equal amounts of onion and stems.
Add crushed garlic and parsley flakes to taste.
Cook in 2 tablespoons margarine until onions are soft.
In mixing bowl, combine 2 eggs; beat well and add 1 cup bread crumbs.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add Parmesan cheese, about 2 tablespoons or more.
If mixture is not real moist, add more melted margarine.
Add cooked stems and onions.
Stuff caps; place in buttered baking dish.
Melt 1/2 stick margarine and stir in mixture; add lemon juice to taste.
Spoon over stuffed caps.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie squares
directions: Combine the first four ingredients and press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients and beat well.
Pour onto baked crust.
Bake 20 minutes.

title: hamburger cheese bake
directions: Brown meat with onion.
Drain.
Mix all ingredients and pour into baking dish.
Top with biscuits and cheese.
Bake until brown and bubbly.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Add sugar to drained sauerkraut and let set in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.

title: italian casserole
directions: Cook pasta shells as directed on package. Drain. Saute the ground beef.
Mix cottage cheese, butter and tomato sauce until well blended.
Stir in mushrooms and green pepper, blending well. Add oregano, salt and pepper.
Place layer of shells in bottom of a lightly buttered casserole dish.
Cover with layer of cottage cheese mixture. Top with half of the pepperoni.
Place 2 slices of cheese on top. Crumble 1/3 ground beef evenly over cheese. Repeat layers, ending with cheese on top ringed with pepperoni.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until hot and bubbly.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat until smooth.
Add flour, soda, salt, milk and bananas and mix well.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 45 to 55 minutes.
Makes one loaf.

title: sweet potato balls *
directions: Boil and skin sweet potatoes.
Beat and sweeten to taste.
Make into balls with marshmallow on the inside.
Roll in cornflake crumbs.
Put into dish and put chips of butter on top.
